WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.093
- YOU WILL NEVER GUESS
WHO I KEEP RUNNING INTO.

00:03.140 --> 00:05.654
JIM KAZINSKY.
- OH, JIM KAZINSKY.

00:05.690 --> 00:07.658
HE WAS REAL CUTE.

00:07.690 --> 00:09.248
- OH, MY GOD.

00:09.280 --> 00:11.202
- YOU'RE MORE BEAUTIFUL
THAN I REMEMBER YOU.

00:11.250 --> 00:13.070
- REALLY?
STOP TALKING.

00:13.110 --> 00:14.657
- I GOT IT.
IT'S NOT ME, IT'S YOU.

00:14.700 --> 00:18.113
- EXACTLY.
IT'S NOT YOU. IT'S ME.

00:18.150 --> 00:19.287
- DADDY, THIS IS STEVE.

00:19.320 --> 00:20.730
- IT'S REALLY GOOD
TO MEET YOU, SIR.

00:20.770 --> 00:22.249
- WHAT'S UP?

00:22.290 --> 00:24.394
- YOU ROBBED ME
OF FIVE YEARS OF MY SON'S LIFE.

00:24.430 --> 00:26.182
- WHY DON'T YOU COME JOIN ME
IN THE LIVING ROOM?

00:26.230 --> 00:28.676
THERE'S SOMETHING
I WANT TO SHOW YOU.

00:35.790 --> 00:38.167
- WELL, YOU WANT TO TELL ME
HOW THIS HAPPENED, BUG?

00:38.210 --> 00:40.269
- YOU KNOW SKIPPY
FROM NEXT DOOR?

00:40.310 --> 00:42.278
HE RAN IN
AND KNOCKED IT DOWN.

00:42.310 --> 00:44.278
- HUH.

00:44.320 --> 00:46.481
YOU KNOW, THE MONROES
DON'T HAVE A DOG ANYMORE.

00:46.520 --> 00:48.101
- SKIPPY CAME BACK.

00:48.150 --> 00:50.482
- SKIPPY'S. ..

00:50.530 --> 00:52.248
SKIPPY WENT TO THE COUNTRY

00:52.290 --> 00:53.769
AFI'ER THAT THING WITH THE CAR.

00:53.810 --> 00:55.186
I DON'T THINK
HE'S COMING BACK.

00:55.220 --> 00:55.879
- WELL, HE DID.

00:55.910 --> 00:57.116
- JOEL, DON'T.

00:57.160 --> 00:59.560
WHOEVER BROKE IT
WILL CLEAN IT UP.

00:59.610 --> 01:01.225
- SKIPPY DOESN'T KNOW
HOW TO CLEAN, MOM.

01:01.260 --> 01:03.080
- SKIPPY DIDN'T
BREAK THE VASE, BUG.

01:03.130 --> 01:05.405
- YES, HE DID.
I SAW HIM.

01:05.440 --> 01:08.125
- THERE'S NO EXCUSE FOR LYING.

01:08.170 --> 01:09.239
- BUT YOU'RE A LIAR.

01:09.270 --> 01:11.135
- NO, BABY, I'M A LAWYER.

01:11.170 --> 01:14.276
- HARMONY'S MOM
SAID THEY'RE THE SAME THING.

01:18.210 --> 01:19.177
- [clears throat]

01:19.210 --> 01:21.178
JUST TELL ME THE TRUTH.

01:21.210 --> 01:22.654
DID YOU BREAK THE VASE?

01:22.700 --> 01:25.146
- NO.
DID YOU?

01:40.230 --> 01:43.199
- HEY, IS THAT
PERIODIC TABLE TEST TODAY?

01:43.240 --> 01:45.162
- OH. UM, NO.

01:45.200 --> 01:46.713
NO, IT'S ACTUALLY MONDAY.

01:46.760 --> 01:48.546
- COOL.
- YEAH.

01:51.620 --> 01:54.623
LOOK.
LET THE GAMES BEGIN.

01:54.660 --> 01:57.834
JEEZ. YOU KNOW, THEY SHOULD
JUST USE THE MONEY FOR THE DANCE

01:57.870 --> 02:00.930
FOR, LIKE, A VENDING MACHINE
OR SOMETHING.

02:00.980 --> 02:03.528
- ACTUALLY, I WAS GONNA GO.

02:03.570 --> 02:05.185
I MEAN, WHY NOT, RIGHT?

02:05.220 --> 02:07.279
- YEAH. YEAH.

02:07.330 --> 02:08.490
- SEE YA.

02:08.540 --> 02:12.226
- OKAY.

02:15.200 --> 02:15.950
DOES IT EVEN MATTER

02:15.990 --> 02:17.548
WHAT I WEAR
TO A SCHOOL DANCE?

02:17.580 --> 02:18.478
- OF COURSE IT MATTERS,

02:18.510 --> 02:19.499
BECAUSE LINDSAY IS THERE,

02:19.550 --> 02:21.165
AND YOU'VE HAD A CRUSH
ON LINDSAY FOR FOREVER,

02:21.210 --> 02:22.370
AND YOU ARE, LIKE,
IN LOVE WITH HER,

02:22.410 --> 02:23.377
AND IF YOU DON'T LOOK GOOD,

02:23.410 --> 02:24.445
SHE'S NOT GONNA BE INTO YOU.

02:24.480 --> 02:28.177
- I NEED YOU TO PICK
FIVE SCHOOLS,

02:28.210 --> 02:30.201
BECAUSE WE ARE GOING
ON YOUR COLLEGE TOUR.

02:30.250 --> 02:31.342
THERE'S A BUNCH
OF CATALOGUES HERE.

02:31.390 --> 02:32.175
- I REALLY THINK
THIS IS CUTE.

02:32.220 --> 02:33.448
WAIT A SECOND.
THE COLLEGE TOUR?

02:33.490 --> 02:34.730
I THOUGHT
WE COULDN'T AFFORD IT.

02:34.770 --> 02:35.930
- YES. NO, WELL,
I PICKED UP EXTRA SHIFTS,

02:35.980 --> 02:37.072
'CAUSE I THINK IT'S IMPORTANT,

02:37.120 --> 02:38.735
AND YOU'RE GONNA COME
WORK WITH ME TOMORROW NIGHT.

02:38.770 --> 02:39.634
- OH, AT THE BAR?

02:39.670 --> 02:41.706
- NO, WE HAVE
A CATERING GIG AT CAL,

02:41.740 --> 02:43.913
- THIS IS IN THE TOP CHOICES.
- AND IT'S A POETRY READING,

02:43.950 --> 02:46.601
AND SO YOU'RE GONNA...
- POETRY READING?

02:46.640 --> 02:49.200
YEAH, I'D ACTUALLY
RATHER SELL AN ORGAN,

02:49.230 --> 02:50.299
BUT THANKS FOR INVITING ME.
- WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT,

02:50.340 --> 02:51.602
IF YOU DON'T CHANGE
THAT ATI'ITUDE,

02:51.650 --> 02:53.265
IT MAY COME TO THAT,
'CAUSE I DON'T THINK

02:53.310 --> 02:54.572
YOU NEED BOTH LIVERS,
ANYWAY.

02:54.620 --> 02:55.951
- WHAT ABOUT THIS?
- THAT'S NOT GOOD.

02:56.000 --> 02:57.069
WHY DO YOU THINK THAT ME

02:57.100 --> 03:00.228
GIVING LI'I'I'LE TINY
HORS D'OEUVRES TO ENGLISH MAJORS

03:00.280 --> 03:02.248
IS GONNA MAKE ME
WANT TO GO TO COLLEGE?

03:02.280 --> 03:04.202
- WELL, WHAT IS GONNA
MAKE YOU WANT TO GO TO COLLEGE?

03:04.250 --> 03:05.524
- NOTHING,
'CAUSE I DON'T WANT TO GO.

03:05.560 --> 03:07.972
- YOU DON'T SEEM TO GET
THAT THIS IS THE YEAR.

03:08.010 --> 03:09.625
THIS IS YOUR JUNIOR YEAR.

03:09.670 --> 03:11.285
THIS IS THE YEAR
THAT IS THE DIFFERENCE

03:11.320 --> 03:13.288
BETWEEN
"PAGING DR. BRAVERMAN"

03:13.330 --> 03:14.945
OR "DO YOU WANT
FRIES WITH THAT?"

03:14.980 --> 03:15.901
THIS IS THE YEAR.

03:15.950 --> 03:16.871
- REALLY? DR. BRAVERMAN?
I DON'T THINK SO.

03:16.920 --> 03:18.911
- YES, IT'S POSSIBLE.
IF YOU JUST--UGH.

03:18.950 --> 03:22.329
JUST PICK FIVE SCHOOLS, AMBER.

03:22.370 --> 03:24.952
WHY IS IT SO HARD?
THAT'S CUTE. WEAR THAT.

03:24.990 --> 03:25.979
- IT'S CUTE, RIGHT?

03:26.030 --> 03:28.407
- HONEY, LISTEN,
IF YOU'RE GONNA WEAR A T-SHIRT,

03:28.440 --> 03:29.953
WEAR A BLAZER, OKAY?

03:30.000 --> 03:31.820
YOU LOOK SO CUTE
IN A BLAZER.

03:31.860 --> 03:32.849
SO CUTE.

03:32.900 --> 03:34.299
- ALL RIGHT.
THANK YOU.

03:39.040 --> 03:41.247
- OH, GOD!

03:41.290 --> 03:42.245
- ELLIOT.

03:42.290 --> 03:43.359
- [laughs]

03:43.390 --> 03:46.632
- ELLIOT. ELLIOT.

03:46.670 --> 03:50.731
[TV continues indistinct]

03:50.780 --> 03:51.735
- OH, COME ON.

03:51.780 --> 03:52.735
HE DIDN'T EVEN MAKE IT

03:52.780 --> 03:53.849
TO THE FLYING BIKES PART.

03:53.880 --> 03:54.812
- IT'S TOO LATE.

03:54.850 --> 03:56.010
- YOU DON'T WANT
TO WAKE HIM UP?

03:56.060 --> 03:57.015
- MM-MM.

03:57.060 --> 04:01.019
- HERE, I'LL GRAB HIM.

04:01.060 --> 04:04.405
OKAY.

04:04.450 --> 04:06.657
- E.T.

04:10.660 --> 04:13.311
- OKAY.

04:13.350 --> 04:15.591
HERE YOU GO, BUDDY.

04:18.010 --> 04:20.695
GOOD NIGHT.

04:48.080 --> 04:49.035
I SHOULD GO.

04:49.080 --> 04:51.036
- YEAH.
- OKAY.

04:51.080 --> 04:53.867
OH.

04:53.910 --> 04:54.729
- HI, HONEY.

04:54.770 --> 04:56.419
GUESS WHAT. GUESS WHAT.
GUESS WHAT.

04:56.460 --> 04:57.802
- WHAT?
- DENISE JUST CALLED,

04:57.840 --> 04:59.353
AND SHE IS ANNOUNCING
HER CANDIDACY

04:59.400 --> 05:01.083
FOR LIEUTENANT GOVERNOR
IN SACRAMENTO THIS WEEKEND.

05:01.120 --> 05:02.678
- REALLY? THAT'S GREAT.
GOOD FOR HER.

05:02.710 --> 05:03.779
- I KNOW. IT'S AMAZING.

05:03.820 --> 05:05.811
AND SHE WANTS ME TO COME DOWN
AND HELP HER OUT.

05:05.850 --> 05:07.056
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
HELP HER WITH HER SPEECHES,

05:07.090 --> 05:08.091
AND THINGS LIKE THAT.

05:08.130 --> 05:09.677
- JUST LIKE OLD TIMES, HUH?

05:09.720 --> 05:10.994
- YEAH, I TOLD HER
THERE'S PROBABLY NO WAY

05:11.030 --> 05:12.850
WITH EVERYTHING
THAT'S GOING ON WITH MAX,

05:12.890 --> 05:14.619
AND HE'S GETTING ACCLIMATED,
AND YOUR WORK--

05:14.650 --> 05:15.856
- WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
YOU SAID NO?

05:15.900 --> 05:17.618
- YEAH, I TOLD HER NO.

05:17.660 --> 05:19.104
- BUT IT'S JUST
FOR THE WEEKEND.

05:19.140 --> 05:20.892
- YEAH, LIKE, THREE DAYS.

05:20.940 --> 05:22.134
- WELL, HONEY,
THIS IS MAJOR.

05:22.180 --> 05:25.069
IT'S HUGE. I MEAN, YOU WERE
WITH HER FROM THE BEGINNING.

05:25.110 --> 05:26.589
- SO SHOULD I DO IT?
ARE YOU TELLING ME TO DO IT?

05:26.630 --> 05:28.109
- YEAH.
- REALLY?

05:28.150 --> 05:30.141
- SOUNDS TO ME LIKE THE FUTURE
LIEUTENANT GOVERNOR NEEDS YOU.

05:30.190 --> 05:31.521
- HONEY, THAT IS SO AWESOME.

05:31.570 --> 05:33.083
I WON'T BE GONE
LONGER THAN THAT. I PROMISE.

05:33.120 --> 05:35.463
WHAT IS THIS?
- I DON'T KNOW.

05:35.500 --> 05:36.569
JUST A LITTLE
SOMETHING-SOMETHING

05:36.610 --> 05:38.328
THAT CAME IN THE MAIL TODAY.

05:39.470 --> 05:40.744
- I THINK
I KNOW WHAT THIS IS.

05:40.780 --> 05:43.055
- I THINK YOU DO TOO.

05:43.100 --> 05:44.362
YOW.
- WOW.

05:44.410 --> 05:45.479
- NICE.

05:45.510 --> 05:46.989
- YOU DIRTY DOG.

05:47.030 --> 05:47.997
HONEY.

05:48.030 --> 05:48.997
- WOOF.

05:49.030 --> 05:50.167
- I HOPE IT FITS ME.

05:50.210 --> 05:52.758
THIS LEFT BOOB IS A LITTLE BIT
BIGGER THAN THE RIGHT.

05:52.800 --> 05:54.108
- I LIKE THAT RIGHT THERE.

05:54.140 --> 05:55.129
[purrs]

05:55.180 --> 05:57.102
- WHAT INSPIRED
THIS LITTLE BIT OF NAUGHTINESS?

05:57.140 --> 05:58.698
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

05:58.730 --> 05:59.867
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

05:59.910 --> 06:01.696
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
WHAT DO I MEAN?

06:01.740 --> 06:03.594
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
WHAT DO I MEAN?

06:03.630 --> 06:06.190
I MEAN, YOU ORDERED IT.

06:06.220 --> 06:08.188
- NO, I DIDN'T.
- YOU DIDN'T?

06:08.220 --> 06:10.154
- NO, I DIDN'T ORDER THIS.

06:10.190 --> 06:12.124
DID YOU LOOK AT THE PACKAGE?

06:12.160 --> 06:13.775
DID IT COME...

06:13.820 --> 06:15.128
HMM.

06:15.160 --> 06:17.128
YOU CAN READ IT.

06:17.160 --> 06:19.640
- "H. BRAVERMAN."

06:21.450 --> 06:22.542
HADDIE?

06:22.580 --> 06:23.683
HAD--GET IT OFF ME.

06:23.720 --> 06:24.891
GET IT OFF. GET IT OFF.

06:24.930 --> 06:27.410
- MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

06:27.450 --> 06:30.101
MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

06:30.140 --> 06:32.415
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

06:32.460 --> 06:34.837
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

06:34.870 --> 06:37.430
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

06:37.460 --> 06:39.667
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

06:39.700 --> 06:41.907
AND MAY YOU STAY

06:41.950 --> 06:44.225
FOREVER YOUNG

06:44.260 --> 06:47.081
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

06:47.130 --> 06:49.121
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

06:49.160 --> 06:51.845
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

06:51.890 --> 06:54.051
AND SEE THE LIGHT
SURROUNDING YOU

06:54.100 --> 06:56.853
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

06:56.890 --> 06:59.029
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

06:59.070 --> 07:01.061
AND MAY YOU STAY

07:01.110 --> 07:03.749
FOREVER YOUNG

07:03.800 --> 07:06.030
MAY YOU STAY

07:06.080 --> 07:09.174
FOREVER YOUNG

07:12.290 --> 07:13.496
- HI.

07:13.530 --> 07:14.497
- OH, HEY, HONEY.

07:14.530 --> 07:15.497
GOOD MORNING.
- MORNING.

07:15.530 --> 07:16.804
- HEY, IS MAX AWAKE YET?

07:16.850 --> 07:18.158
- UM, YEAH,
I THINK HE'S JUST CHANGING.

07:18.190 --> 07:19.669
- OH, OKAY, GOOD.

07:19.710 --> 07:21.564
OH, BEFORE I FORGET,

07:21.610 --> 07:24.670
A PACKAGE
CAME FOR YOU YESTERDAY.

07:24.720 --> 07:25.982
FROM VICTORIA'S SECRET?

07:26.030 --> 07:27.509
IT GOT OPENED ACCIDENTALLY.

07:27.550 --> 07:29.882
I'M NOT SURE HOW.
IT JUST--

07:30.620 --> 07:32.064
-MOM?
-HMM?

07:32.100 --> 07:34.239
- HOW WOULD A PACKAGE
WITH MY NAME ON IT

07:34.280 --> 07:35.440
GET OPENED ACCIDENTALLY?

07:36.140 --> 07:37.516
- WELL, I THINK YOUR FATHER

07:37.560 --> 07:38.686
ASSUMED THAT IT WAS FOR ME,

07:38.730 --> 07:40.960
SO THEREFORE HE OPENED IT.
- OH, THAT'S REALLY GROSS.

07:41.010 --> 07:43.035
- ANYWAY, HE THREW IT AWAY,
SO IT DOESN'T MATTER.

07:43.080 --> 07:43.933
- WHAT?
- MM-HMM.

07:43.980 --> 07:45.242
HE WAS GONNA BURN IT,
BUT, YOU KNOW,

07:45.290 --> 07:46.837
HE FIGURED PROBABLY NOT
A GOOD IDEA.

07:46.880 --> 07:48.279
- MOM,
I SPENT MY MONEY ON THAT.

07:48.320 --> 07:49.287
THAT'S EXPENSIVE.

07:49.330 --> 07:50.524
- I KNOW THAT YOU DID.

07:50.570 --> 07:54.779
THAT'S WHY I RESCUED IT.

07:54.810 --> 07:57.085
- THANK YOU.

07:57.130 --> 08:00.987
- SO, HADDIE, CAN I
JUST ASK YOU A QUESTION?

08:01.030 --> 08:03.305
WHY WOULD YOU BUY YOURSELF
A BRA LIKE THAT?

08:03.340 --> 08:05.023
- I'M NOT GONNA
TALK ABOUT THIS WITH YOU.

08:05.070 --> 08:06.617
- OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?
THAT'S FINE.

08:06.650 --> 08:08.026
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO TALK
TO DAD ABOUT IT, THEN,

08:08.070 --> 08:09.753
BECAUSE HE'S REALLY CURIOUS
AS TO WHY...

08:09.790 --> 08:11.109
- OH, YOU WOULD NOT DO THAT.
- YES, I WOULD.

08:11.140 --> 08:12.175
I'LL CALL HIM RIGHT NOW.

08:13.210 --> 08:15.838
- ALL RIGHT. WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO KNOW? JUST ASK.

08:15.870 --> 08:17.758
- DID YOU BUY THAT BRA
FOR STEVE?

08:17.800 --> 08:20.075
- MOM...
- HMM?

08:20.120 --> 08:21.690
- YOU KNOW STEVE
DOESN'T HAVE BOOBS.

08:21.740 --> 08:23.560
I'M NOT GONNA BUY HIM A BRA.

08:23.600 --> 08:24.942
DON'T BE RIDICULOUS.

08:24.980 --> 08:27.608
- HADDIE,
DID YOU BUY IT FOR STEVE?

08:27.640 --> 08:30.939
- NO, OKAY? I BOUGHT IT
FOR MYSELF, ALL RIGHT?

08:30.990 --> 08:32.708
IT'S PRETTY AND IT'S SEXY,

08:32.750 --> 08:34.786
AND, I MEAN, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU WANT TO THINK ABOUT ME,

08:34.820 --> 08:35.605
BUT I'M A WOMAN.

08:35.650 --> 08:37.197
- YOU HAVE
TO PROMISE ME SOMETHING.

08:37.240 --> 08:38.992
YOU HAVE TO PROMISE ME
THAT YOU'RE BEING SMART,

08:39.030 --> 08:40.850
AND YOU'RE BEING CAREFUL,

08:40.890 --> 08:42.164
AND YOU'RE NOT HAVING SEX.

08:42.210 --> 08:44.098
- WHAT DO YOU THINK SEX IS?

08:44.140 --> 08:46.176
- I DON'T KNOW.
ANYTHING BEYOND MAKING OUT, OR--

08:46.210 --> 08:47.245
- THAT'S YOUR DEFINITION
OF SEX?

08:47.280 --> 08:49.202
- FOR YOU.

08:49.250 --> 08:51.866
- I THINK I HAVE
TO GET READY FOR SCHOOL.

08:51.910 --> 08:53.866
LIKE YOU SAID,
I CAN'T BE LATE AGAIN.

08:53.910 --> 08:56.117
- I TRUST YOU.

08:59.120 --> 09:01.042
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU THINK YOU MADE OUT WITH HER?

09:01.090 --> 09:02.114
- IT'S THE MOTHER
OF MY CHILD.

09:02.160 --> 09:04.185
- SO WHAT, THAT'S SOMEHOW
WARPED YOUR MEMORY?

09:04.230 --> 09:05.777
- I WATCHED THE VIDEO

09:05.820 --> 09:07.913
OF MY SON COMING OUT
OF HER INSIDES.

09:07.960 --> 09:09.643
- OH, OH,
HUGE MISTAKE FOR YOU.

09:09.680 --> 09:10.647
- YEAH.
- YEAH.

09:10.680 --> 09:11.851
- HUGE MISTAKE.

09:11.890 --> 09:13.881
- YEAH, NO MAN SHOULD HAVE
TO WITNESS THAT UNPREPARED.

09:13.930 --> 09:15.090
LEAST OF ALL YOU.
- IT'S EXTREME.

09:15.140 --> 09:16.368
- YEAH, YOU THINK
YOU'RE GONNA RECOVER?

09:16.410 --> 09:18.890
- DOES IT RECOVER?

09:18.930 --> 09:20.170
- YEAH.
YEAH, IT DOES. IN TIME.

09:20.210 --> 09:21.245
- SO KRISTINA IS...?

09:21.280 --> 09:22.963
- A--BA, BA, BA.

09:23.010 --> 09:24.034
- OKAY.

09:24.900 --> 09:26.140
- WHAT DO YOU THINK?
YOU GUYS GONNA GET TOGETHER?

09:26.180 --> 09:27.215
- YOU KNOW,
I THINK IT'S SAFER

09:27.250 --> 09:28.979
IF WE JUST STAY FRIENDS.

09:29.010 --> 09:30.352
- YEAH, THAT'S GOOD.
YOU BETTER PLAY IT SAFE.

09:30.390 --> 09:31.630
YEAH. GOOD IDEA.

09:31.670 --> 09:34.218
- WELL, LOOK, IT'S NOT LIKE
I CAN WALK AWAY FROM THIS ONE.

09:34.260 --> 09:35.284
- GOOD FOR YOU, CROSBY.

09:35.330 --> 09:36.729
- BUT THEN AGAIN,
I'M ONLY HUMAN.

09:36.780 --> 09:38.702
SHE'S VERY ATTRACTIVE.
SO I DON'T KNOW.

09:38.750 --> 09:40.126
- ALL RIGHT, WELL,
WHAT DOES JASMINE

09:40.160 --> 09:41.843
THINK ABOUT ALL THIS?
- I DON'T KNOW.

09:41.890 --> 09:43.744
- WELL, HAVE YOU CONSIDERED
MAYBE ASKING HER?

09:43.790 --> 09:46.020
- YOU KNOW, I JUST--I WISH
THAT WE COULD JUST HANG OUT,

09:46.060 --> 09:48.028
YOU KNOW, WITH NO KID,
JUST THE TWO OF US,

09:48.070 --> 09:50.026
AND KIND OF
GET TO KNOW EACH OTHER AGAIN,

09:50.070 --> 09:52.129
BUT, YOU KNOW, NOW THE CART'S
IN FRONT OF THE HORSE.

09:52.170 --> 09:53.649
IT'S LIKE--
- WELL, THERE IS SOMETHING

09:53.690 --> 09:55.203
THAT PEOPLE DO
IN SITUATIONS LIKE THIS.

09:55.240 --> 09:57.720
IT'S CALLED DATING.
- HMM.

09:57.760 --> 09:59.239
- HOW'S IT GOING, KRISTINA?

09:59.280 --> 10:01.908
- IT'S--I HAVE A COUPLE OF
CHOICES THAT I THINK MIGHT WORK.

10:01.940 --> 10:04.249
- COME ON.
- LET'S SEE 'EM.

10:04.290 --> 10:06.212
- TA-DA! HOW DO I LOOK?

10:06.260 --> 10:07.739
- UM...

10:07.770 --> 10:09.249
- FROM THE DAVID BYRNE
COLLECTION.

10:09.290 --> 10:10.939
- WHO'S DAVID BYRNE?
- JOAN COLLINS?

10:10.980 --> 10:12.299
- CYBIL SHEPHERD'S
LOST JACKET.

10:12.330 --> 10:13.638
- YOU'RE MAKING FUN OF ME,
AREN'T YOU?

10:13.680 --> 10:14.669
- WERE YOU ON DYNASTY?

10:14.710 --> 10:16.223
- I CAN'T DO IT.

10:16.270 --> 10:17.225
- IT'S LIKE AN EPISODE
OF HOARDERS.

10:17.270 --> 10:18.988
WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU CLEANED THAT CLOSET?

10:19.030 --> 10:20.258
- OH, MY GOD.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

10:20.300 --> 10:21.779
MY DAUGHTER HAS A BETTER
WARDROBE THAN I DO.

10:21.820 --> 10:22.923
- KRISTINA,
LET ME FIND SOMETHING.

10:22.960 --> 10:24.234
- WE'LL HELP YOU.
SHE'LL HELP.

10:24.270 --> 10:26.443
- OH, BY THE WAY,
GUESS WHO STARTED BUYING BRAS.

10:26.480 --> 10:28.653
- WHO?
- FROM "VICTORIA SECRETS?"

10:28.690 --> 10:30.066
- YOU?
- HADDIE.

10:30.110 --> 10:31.134
- UH-OH.
- WELL, THAT'S OKAY.

10:31.180 --> 10:32.272
- YES.
VERY SEXY BRAS.

10:32.320 --> 10:34.072
- HOW BAD IS IT?
WHAT'S THE LACE TO BASE?

10:34.110 --> 10:35.418
- THE WHAT?
- IF IT'S REALLY LACEY,

10:35.460 --> 10:37.667
IT MEANS SHE'S GOING FURTHER
ON THE "BASEY."

10:37.700 --> 10:39.907
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
SHE'S NOT DOING ANY OF THAT.

10:39.940 --> 10:40.759
- FIRST BASE IS KISSING.

10:40.810 --> 10:42.425
SECOND BASE IS--
WHAT IS SECOND BASE?

10:42.460 --> 10:44.280
- THERE'S A LOT OF LACE,
BUT SHE'S NOT DOING ANY OF THAT.

10:44.330 --> 10:46.981
- OKAY, SECOND BASE
IS READING TENNYSON.

10:47.020 --> 10:48.157
- OKAY, STOP IT.
- OKAY.

10:48.190 --> 10:50.294
AND, UM, CAN I
ASK YOU GUYS SOMETHING?

10:50.330 --> 10:52.434
WHEN DID YOUR CHILDREN
START LYING TO YOU?

10:52.470 --> 10:54.165
- UH, IT WAS IN THE HOSPITAL,
I THINK.

10:54.200 --> 10:56.953
AMBER WAS BORN, AND SHE SAID,
"IT WASN'T MY VODKA."

10:57.000 --> 10:58.444
- REALLY?
- OOH, HADDIE WAS TWO.

10:58.480 --> 11:00.209
SHE SWORE TO ME
THAT SHE DID NOT

11:00.240 --> 11:01.309
STICK A LITTLE BEAD
UP HER NOSE,

11:01.350 --> 11:02.965
AND THE DOCTOR PULLED IT OUT

11:03.000 --> 11:04.308
AND WAS LIKE,
"HERE'S THE BEAD."

11:04.350 --> 11:05.965
- SO THIS IS NORMAL?
THAT'S WHAT KIDS DO...

11:06.010 --> 11:07.272
- ESPECIALLY IN YOUR FAMILY.

11:07.320 --> 11:08.799
- WAIT. WHAT?

11:08.840 --> 11:11.729
- ESPECIALLY, YOU KNOW,
SHE'D LEARN IT FROM YOU.

11:11.770 --> 11:12.839
- WHY?

11:13.840 --> 11:16.070
- 'CAUSE YOU'RE A--
A LAWYER.

11:17.260 --> 11:18.045
THEY LIE.

11:18.090 --> 11:20.183
- OKAY, I'M NOT
GONNA GO INTO IT.

11:20.230 --> 11:21.709
- LISTEN, I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T MEAN THAT.

11:21.750 --> 11:22.978
IT WAS JUST A JOKE.

11:23.020 --> 11:24.464
YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL.
YOU'RE SO SUCCESSFUL.

11:24.510 --> 11:25.886
YOU'RE AMAZING AT YOUR JOB.

11:25.920 --> 11:27.808
THERE'S NO BETTER
ROLE MODEL OUT THERE.

11:27.850 --> 11:29.238
I SERVE LIQUOR FOR A LIVING,

11:29.270 --> 11:30.919
AND I DIDN'T GO TO COLLEGE,

11:30.960 --> 11:32.188
AND NOW AMBER
DOESN'T WANT TO GO,

11:32.240 --> 11:33.400
'CAUSE I'M SUCH
A GREAT ROLE MODEL, 50--

11:33.450 --> 11:34.519
- WAIT.
AMBER DOESN'T WANT TO GO?

11:34.550 --> 11:35.710
- SHE'S GOTTA GO
TO COLLEGE.

11:35.760 --> 11:37.239
- I CAN'T MAKE HER
DO ANYTHING.

11:37.280 --> 11:38.417
- SHE'S GOING TO COLLEGE.
- YES.

11:38.450 --> 11:40.247
- OKAY, I MEAN, YEAH.

11:40.280 --> 11:42.202
- YOU KNOW WHAT THE PROBLEM
IS FOR MOTHERS?

11:42.250 --> 11:43.831
- DAUGHTERS.
- DAUGHTERS.

11:43.870 --> 11:44.723
- AMEN.

11:44.770 --> 11:45.486
[doorbell rings]

11:48.150 --> 11:49.902
- HEY, DREW.
COME ON IN.

11:49.950 --> 11:51.042
- OH, THANKS.

11:51.080 --> 11:52.354
HEY, MAX.
- YOU ALL RIGHT?

11:52.400 --> 11:53.355
- YEAH, I'M FINE, BUT...

11:53.400 --> 11:54.355
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

11:54.400 --> 11:56.322
- OH, UM...

11:56.370 --> 12:00.192
OKAY, BASICALLY, THERE'S
A SCHOOL DANCE COMING UP,

12:00.230 --> 12:02.050
AND I'M REALLY
NERVOUS ABOUT IT,

12:02.100 --> 12:03.852
BECAUSE I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO DANCE.

12:03.890 --> 12:05.118
THAT'S BASICALLY
WHY I'M HERE.

12:05.170 --> 12:06.307
AND I DIDN'T WANT
TO ASK SOMEONE

12:06.340 --> 12:07.853
WHO'S GONNA HUMILIATE ME,

12:07.890 --> 12:08.857
MY SISTER OR SOMETHING.

12:08.900 --> 12:10.231
- ALL RIGHT, DREW,
SAY NO MORE.

12:10.280 --> 12:11.508
LOOK, I DON'T WANT
TO TOOT MY OWN HORN,

12:11.550 --> 12:13.370
BUT WHEN I WAS
IN HIGH SCHOOL

12:13.420 --> 12:16.241
PEOPLE USED
TO CALL ME "FEVER."

12:16.280 --> 12:18.214
SATURDAY NIGHT FEVER?
JOHN TRAVOLTA?

12:18.250 --> 12:19.865
- OH, I HAVEN'T REALLY
SEEN IT, BUT...

12:19.910 --> 12:21.138
- DOESN'T MATTER.
TELL YOU WHAT.

12:21.180 --> 12:22.420
COME ON, HELP ME CLEAR OUT
SOME SPACE HERE.

12:22.460 --> 12:24.189
I'LL SHOW YOU A FEW MOVES.

12:24.220 --> 12:25.187
ALL RIGHT, NOW LISTEN.

12:25.220 --> 12:26.187
MOST IMPORTANT THING,

12:26.220 --> 12:27.869
YOU GOT TO JUST RELAX.

12:27.910 --> 12:29.775
YOU GOT TO SHUT THIS OFF,

12:29.810 --> 12:30.777
TURN THIS ON.

12:30.810 --> 12:32.152
THAT'S ALL I'M SAYING, OKAY?

12:32.190 --> 12:33.327
- I'M REALLY TRYING.

12:33.370 --> 12:34.917
- LET ME FIND
THE RIGHT PIECE OF MUSIC.

12:34.960 --> 12:37.849
ALL RIGHT.
[Run-DMC's It's Tricky plays]

12:37.890 --> 12:40.438
JUST FEEL THE MUSIC.

12:40.480 --> 12:43.404
- NO...

12:43.450 --> 12:45.236
I MEAN, THANK YOU, BUT...
- FEEL THE MUSIC.

12:45.280 --> 12:46.827
- NO, I MEANT, LIKE...

12:46.860 --> 12:48.248
I MEANT MORE LIKE
SLOW-DANCING TYPE OF...

12:48.280 --> 12:49.793
- I KNOW SLOWDANCING,

12:49.830 --> 12:51.206
BUT IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT THE MUSIC IS, MAN.

12:51.250 --> 12:53.343
YOU JUST GOT TO--YOU GOT
TO FEEL THAT IN YOUR BODY.

12:53.390 --> 12:54.345
START HERE.
- OH, YEAH, SORRY.

12:54.390 --> 12:56.176
- YOU MIGHT FEEL IT
IN YOUR LEGS, YOUR ARMS,

12:56.220 --> 12:58.359
YOUR FEET, SHOULDERS,
YOUR RIB CAGE.

12:58.390 --> 13:00.039
ALL OVER.

13:00.080 --> 13:01.251
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

13:01.290 --> 13:02.154
- NO, BUT NOT LIKE THAT.

13:02.190 --> 13:05.227
LIKE--LIKE WITH A PARTNER
TYPE OF--

13:05.260 --> 13:06.534
SLOW-DANCING TYPE OF THING.

13:06.570 --> 13:08.458
NOT LIKE...

13:08.510 --> 13:10.296
- HEY, YOU GUYS. DREW'S GOT
A LITTLE DANCE COMING UP.

13:10.340 --> 13:11.295
I'M JUST SHOWING HIM
A FEW MOVES.

13:11.340 --> 13:12.819
YOU KNOW WHAT, DREW,

13:12.860 --> 13:14.475
YOU MIGHT EVEN WANT
TO THROW SOME BIG STUFF.

13:14.510 --> 13:15.852
YOU KNOW, SOME OF THE--HO!
OOH!

13:15.890 --> 13:18.233
- OH, NO, HE'S GONNA
PUT HIS BACK OUT AGAIN.

13:18.280 --> 13:19.963
- NO, I LIKE IT.
- COME ON, DREW. GET OUT HERE.

13:20.000 --> 13:21.991
MOST IMPORTANT THING TO DO
IS BE CONFIDENT, OKAY?

13:22.040 --> 13:23.826
YOU ASK A GIRL TO DANCE
WITH CONFIDENCE,

13:23.870 --> 13:24.859
SHE CAN'T SAY NO.

13:24.900 --> 13:26.276
- I'M SORRY.
THANK YOU, THOUGH.

13:26.320 --> 13:28.242
- LET ME SHOW YOU
HOW IT'S DONE.

13:28.290 --> 13:29.860
- ALL RIGHT.
WHO'S READY FOR A PARTY?

13:29.910 --> 13:31.935
- UH-OH.
DID HE TELL YOU ABOUT THE FEVER?

13:31.980 --> 13:33.208
- YEAH.
- HE DID?

13:33.260 --> 13:34.909
ONCE YOU UNLEASH THE FEVER,
IT DOESN'T STOP.

13:34.950 --> 13:36.178
- WHOO!

13:36.220 --> 13:37.016
- BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

13:37.050 --> 13:39.564
IT'S HARD
NOT TO CATCH THE FEVER.

13:39.610 --> 13:42.465
- I'M DOING MY BEST.

13:42.510 --> 13:44.432
- IT'S TRICKY
TO ROCK A RHYME

13:44.470 --> 13:46.290
TO ROCK A RHYME
THAT'S RIGHT ON TIME

13:46.340 --> 13:48.331
IT'S TRICKY

13:48.370 --> 13:51.089
TRICKY, TRICKY,
TRICKY, TRICKY

13:51.140 --> 13:54.371
- YOU CAME ALL THIS WAY
FOR A SOCK?

13:54.410 --> 13:56.651
- YEAH, WELL, I JUST
COULDN'T STOP THINKING

13:56.690 --> 13:59.102
ABOUT JABBAR
WITH ONE COLD FOOT,

13:59.140 --> 14:00.584
AND THEN GET FROSTBITE,

14:00.630 --> 14:02.450
AND THEN HAVE A LIMP,
AND...

14:02.490 --> 14:03.457
YOU KNOW.

14:03.490 --> 14:05.003
- THANKS.

14:05.050 --> 14:07.359
HE'LL, UH--I'M SURE
HE'LL APPRECIATE IT.

14:07.390 --> 14:11.019
- OKAY. GOOD.

14:11.050 --> 14:14.110
LOOK, I KNOW
THIS IS KIND OF WEIRD.

14:14.160 --> 14:15.229
I MEAN,
WE ALREADY HAVE A KID,

14:15.260 --> 14:17.080
AND I'M KIND OF
DOING THIS BACKWARDS,

14:17.130 --> 14:19.360
BUT I WANT
TO GET TO KNOW YOU.

14:19.410 --> 14:21.196
I WANT
TO SPEND TIME WITH YOU.

14:21.230 --> 14:24.370
YOU KNOW?

14:24.410 --> 14:27.231
I'D LIKE TO GO OUT
TO DINNER WITH YOU AND TALK,

14:27.280 --> 14:30.306
WITHOUT ANY FLYING BICYCLES

14:30.350 --> 14:32.306
OR EXTRATERRESTRIALS
OR KIDS.

14:32.350 --> 14:35.934
- YOU MEAN A DATE.

14:35.970 --> 14:36.937
- YEAH.

14:36.970 --> 14:40.212
YOU WANT TO DO THAT?

14:40.250 --> 14:42.138
- YEAH. I GUESS.

14:42.190 --> 14:45.318
- OH. WELL, I'M ONLY TAKING
A "YES," SO...

14:48.610 --> 14:50.703
- YES.

14:50.750 --> 14:52.263
- OKAY.

14:52.300 --> 14:53.119
- OKAY.

14:53.160 --> 14:55.333
- I GUESS I WILL
SEE YOU ON SATURDAY.

14:55.370 --> 14:57.509
- I GUESS YOU SHALL.

15:05.450 --> 15:07.247
- HOW DO I LOOK?
DO I LOOK OKAY?

15:07.280 --> 15:08.383
DOES THIS SUIT LOOK OKAY?
- YEAH.

15:08.420 --> 15:09.273
- IT'S NICE, RIGHT?
- YES.

15:09.320 --> 15:10.548
- OKAY, LISTEN,
I WANT YOU TO CALL ME

15:10.590 --> 15:11.727
IF ANYTHING COMES UP AT ALL.

15:11.770 --> 15:12.623
- OKAY.

15:12.670 --> 15:14.388
- I NEED YOU TO HELP DAD
WITH MAX, OKAY?

15:14.430 --> 15:16.182
- RIGHT.

15:16.220 --> 15:17.255
- I TRUST YOU.

15:17.290 --> 15:19.087
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

15:19.120 --> 15:21.111
MAX, HONEY,
LOOK AT MOM.

15:21.160 --> 15:23.321
I NEED YOU TO BE A GOOD BOY
FOR ME THIS WEEKEND, OKAY?

15:23.370 --> 15:25.326
- I ALREADY SAID--
I ALREADY SAID THAT I WOULD.

15:25.370 --> 15:27.122
- SEE? WHY AM I DOING THIS?
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

15:27.160 --> 15:28.229
WHY AM I GOING?

15:28.270 --> 15:29.362
- HEY, HEY, HEY,
IT'S OKAY.

15:29.410 --> 15:30.479
YOU'RE GONNA GO,

15:30.510 --> 15:33.263
AND YOU'RE GONNA KICK
SOME POLITICAL ASS, OKAY?

15:33.310 --> 15:34.265
LOVE YOU.

15:34.310 --> 15:35.379
- I LOVE YOU TOO.

15:35.410 --> 15:36.581
- ALL RIGHT.
- YOU SURE?

15:36.620 --> 15:39.305
- I'M GONNA BE FINE. ALL RIGHT?
- OKAY, YEP.

15:39.350 --> 15:40.374
- ALL RIGHT.
WE'RE PROUD OF YOU, HONEY.

15:40.420 --> 15:41.580
- OKAY.

15:41.630 --> 15:43.279
- SHE THINKS SHE'S GOING
ON A PILGRIMAGE.

15:43.320 --> 15:44.389
- WOULD YOU KNOCK IT OFF?

15:44.420 --> 15:46.217
HEY, DRIVE SAFELY.

15:46.250 --> 15:50.732
- [sighs] BYE.
- ALL RIGHT.

15:50.770 --> 15:54.661
[cell phone rings]

15:54.710 --> 15:56.325
HELLO.

15:56.360 --> 15:58.328
- HONEY?
- HI, HONEY.

15:58.370 --> 16:00.122
- DO NOT FORGET TO DEFROST
THE DINNER THAT I MADE FOR YOU.

16:00.160 --> 16:01.263
- I WON'T FORGET.
- IT'S MEATLOAF.

16:01.300 --> 16:02.608
- I WON'T FORGET.
- OKAY.

16:02.650 --> 16:03.981
THIS IS A MISTAKE.

16:04.030 --> 16:05.406
- NO, KRISTINA,
I WANT THIS FOR YOU.

16:05.440 --> 16:06.611
OKAY, PLEASE,
LET ME DO THIS FOR YOU.

16:06.650 --> 16:09.232
I CAN HANDLE IT.
I LOVE YOU.

16:09.270 --> 16:11.090
- I LOVE YOU TOO.

16:13.450 --> 16:14.439
- GET OUT OF HERE.

16:14.490 --> 16:15.445
- OKAY.

16:15.490 --> 16:17.037
[phone beeps]

16:17.070 --> 16:18.139
- OKAY, I'M GOING.

16:18.180 --> 16:19.249
- WE'RE GOOD.
- I'M LEAVING.

16:19.280 --> 16:21.384
- ALL RIGHT, GOOD-BYE.
- I LOVE YOU.

16:25.290 --> 16:26.382
- AND DO YOU KNOW WHO WROTE

16:26.430 --> 16:28.216
THE DECLARATION
OF INDEPENDENCE?

16:28.260 --> 16:29.807
- MM...YOU?

16:29.850 --> 16:33.058
- NO, NOT ME.
THOMAS JEFFERSON.

16:33.090 --> 16:34.296
YOU HEARD OF HIM?
- NO.

16:34.330 --> 16:35.467
- OKAY.
WELL, HE WAS ONE OF

16:35.510 --> 16:37.432
THE FOUNDING FATHERS
OF THIS COUNTRY,

16:37.470 --> 16:38.744
HE WAS OUR THIRD PRESIDENT,

16:38.790 --> 16:40.781
AND YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE
HE WAS?

16:40.820 --> 16:42.196
- MM, NO.

16:42.240 --> 16:43.161
- HE WAS A LAWYER.

16:43.200 --> 16:45.407
AS WAS OUR SECOND PRESIDENT,
JOHN ADAMS,

16:45.450 --> 16:46.781
AND MANY OF OUR
PRESIDENTS SINCE THEN.

16:46.830 --> 16:48.479
THIS COUNTRY
WAS CREATED BY LAWYERS.

16:48.520 --> 16:51.796
SO WHEN HARMONY'S MOM
SAYS THAT LAWYERS ARE LIARS,

16:51.830 --> 16:53.798
SHE'S NOT
JUST ABSOLUTELY WRONG,

16:53.840 --> 16:55.649
SHE'S KIND OF
INSULTING AMERICA ITSELF.

16:55.700 --> 16:57.042
- AND WE'RE AMERICANS?

16:57.080 --> 16:58.809
- WE'RE AMERICANS.
THAT'S RIGHT.

16:58.840 --> 17:00.216
AND WE'RE AN HONEST PEOPLE.

17:00.260 --> 17:01.454
SO THINK ABOUT THAT,
OKAY?

17:01.500 --> 17:02.455
- 'KAY.
- OKAY.

17:02.500 --> 17:03.467
'CAUSE TELLING THE TRUTH

17:03.500 --> 17:06.185
IS VERY,
VERY, VERY IMPORTANT.

17:06.230 --> 17:08.437
- OKAY.

17:08.470 --> 17:13.225
- SO IS THERE ANYTHING
THAT YOU WANT TO TELL ME?

17:13.270 --> 17:16.376
- MM...

17:16.410 --> 17:20.779
WHEN'S JABBAR COMING OVER?

17:20.830 --> 17:24.345
- JABBAR'S
COMING OVER TONIGHT.

17:24.380 --> 17:27.725
- LOOK AT ALL THESE PEOPLE
DOING SUCH INTERESTING THINGS.

17:27.770 --> 17:29.249
YOU KNOW?
LOOK AT THIS.

17:29.280 --> 17:30.281
ISN'T IT INSPIRING?
IT'S SO BEAUTIFUL.

17:30.320 --> 17:31.594
- I'LL NEVER GET IN HERE.
- THAT'S NOT TRUE.

17:31.630 --> 17:33.143
- DO YOU KNOW
HOW HARD IT IS

17:33.190 --> 17:34.043
TO GET INTO THIS SCHOOL?
- WELL, YOU HAVEN'T TRIED YET.

17:34.080 --> 17:35.149
I MEAN, JUST THINK ABOUT
ALL THE STUFF

17:35.190 --> 17:36.259
THAT HAPPENED IN THE '605,

17:36.290 --> 17:39.088
AND THE, YOU KNOW,
THE NOBEL PRIZE WINNER PEOPLE

17:39.120 --> 17:40.087
WHO WERE HERE.

17:40.120 --> 17:41.326
AND YOU JUST
STAY UP ALL NIGHT,

17:41.370 --> 17:43.224
YOU KNOW,
TALKING AND THINKING,

17:43.260 --> 17:44.431
AND SMOKE--
I MEAN, NOT SMOKE.

17:44.470 --> 17:45.437
DON'T SMOKE.

17:45.470 --> 17:47.222
[phone rings]

17:47.270 --> 17:50.159
[overlapping chatter]

17:50.200 --> 17:51.428
- SO HAPPY TO BE HERE.

17:51.480 --> 17:52.708
- OF COURSE. OF COURSE.

17:52.760 --> 17:54.136
ALL RIGHT, HEADS UP, GUYS.

17:54.170 --> 17:55.478
HEADS UP FOR A SECOND.

17:55.520 --> 17:57.203
THIS IS KRISTINA BRAVERMAN.

17:57.240 --> 17:58.798
SHE HELPED ME
ON MY VERY FIRST CAMPAIGN

17:58.830 --> 18:00.411
WHEN I RAN FOR SCHOOL BOARD.

18:00.450 --> 18:02.657
SHE HELPED ME
WRITE MY PLATFORM,

18:02.700 --> 18:04.725
AND BASICALLY
GOT ME ELECTED.

18:04.770 --> 18:06.522
- OH, I DID NOT.
- YES, YOU DID.

18:06.560 --> 18:07.697
- NO, I DIDN'T.
- YES, YOU DID.

18:07.740 --> 18:09.662
- OKAY.
- LISTEN, SHE IS A GREAT ASSET.

18:09.700 --> 18:11.588
USE HER.
THANKS.

18:11.640 --> 18:13.119
- BUSY.

18:13.160 --> 18:14.149
- UGH. THANK YOU
SO MUCH FOR COMING.

18:14.190 --> 18:16.112
I WAS SO HAPPY
WHEN YOU SAID YOU WERE COMING.

18:16.160 --> 18:17.468
- IT'S BEEN SO LONG.

18:17.510 --> 18:18.602
- I WANT TO HEAR
ALL ABOUT THE FAMILY.

18:18.640 --> 18:20.460
WE NEED TO CATCH UP.
- YEAH, MAX IS A LITTLE BIT...

18:20.510 --> 18:22.364
- HAVE A DRINK LATER?
- YEAH, OF COURSE...

18:22.410 --> 18:24.401
- OH, MY GOD. LISTEN,
I'VE GOT TO GO SHAKE SOME TREES.

18:24.440 --> 18:26.169
I'M SORRY. WE'LL TALK.
WE'LL CATCH UP LATER.

18:26.200 --> 18:28.589
- GOOD LUCK.

18:34.630 --> 18:36.484
SHOULD I SIT HERE?
- YEAH.

18:36.520 --> 18:37.691
- SO WHAT'S GOING ON?

18:37.730 --> 18:40.176
- DUDE, HAVE YOU NAILED DOWN
THE BROWN ENDORSEMENT YET?

18:40.220 --> 18:41.903
- DUDE, I'M WORKING
ALL THE ANGLES I CAN.

18:41.940 --> 18:44.147
- UM, I--I ACTUALLY KNOW
SOMEBODY THAT KNOWS JERRY.

18:44.190 --> 18:47.398
LET ME CHECK.
JERRY BROWN...

18:47.430 --> 18:48.601
OR AT LEAST I USED TO...

18:48.640 --> 18:51.291
- KRISTINA?
- YEAH. YOU CAN CALL ME DUDE.

18:51.330 --> 18:52.706
- COULD YOU
GET SOMETHING TOGETHER

18:52.750 --> 18:54.331
ON THE ASSEMBLYWOMAN'S
POSITIONS

18:54.370 --> 18:55.291
ON EDUCATION
AND THE ENVIRONMENT?

18:55.340 --> 18:57.331
- UM, YEAH,
ACTUALLY THINK I HAVE COPIES

18:57.370 --> 18:59.338
OF HER POSITION PAPERS
RIGHT HERE.

18:59.370 --> 19:01.372
- WE WERE THINKING MORE
ALONG THE LINES OF SOME TWEETS?

19:01.410 --> 19:03.332
140 CHARACTERS OR LESS.

19:03.380 --> 19:05.519
- A TWEET, HUH?

19:05.550 --> 19:08.724
- DO WE HAVE SECURITY
FOR HER SPEECH TONIGHT?

19:10.390 --> 19:12.449
- ALL RIGHT, MAX,
TIME TO TURN OFF THAT TV.

19:14.290 --> 19:15.245
- WHAT?

19:15.290 --> 19:17.178
UH, WAIT.
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

19:17.220 --> 19:19.381
HOLD ON ONE SECOND THERE.
MAX, THIS IS WHAT--

19:19.430 --> 19:20.499
- DAD, I ALREADY OKAYED
THIS WITH MOM, SO...

19:20.530 --> 19:23.294
- I TURNED IT OFF
FOR 20 MINUTES THIS AFTERNOON.

19:23.330 --> 19:24.319
YOU OWE ME.
- WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

19:24.370 --> 19:25.564
- I'M GOING TO STEVE'S
HOUSE AND DON'T WORRY...

19:25.610 --> 19:26.599
- AND THAT IS NOT THE WAY
THAT IT WORKS, AND YOU KNOW IT.

19:26.640 --> 19:28.676
- MOM LETS ME.
- HIS PARENTS ARE HOME, SO...

19:28.710 --> 19:29.813
DON'T FREAK OUT OR ANYTHING.
- WELL, I'M NOT MOM, OKAY?

19:29.850 --> 19:32.296
AND, YOU,
PUT ON A JACKET, OKAY?

19:32.340 --> 19:33.614
- OKAY. DO YOU KNOW
WHERE THE GUM IS?

19:33.650 --> 19:34.856
- NO, I DON'T KNOW
WHERE THE GUM IS.

19:34.890 --> 19:36.448
- I'M NOT COLD REALLY, DAD.

19:36.930 --> 19:38.989
- HEY.
- HEY.

19:39.030 --> 19:40.657
WAIT,
ISN'T THE DANCE TONIGHT?

19:40.690 --> 19:42.794
- UH, YEAH.
I DON'T KNOW.

19:42.830 --> 19:44.513
I'D RATHER JUST
WATCH THE GIANTS, YOU KNOW,

19:44.560 --> 19:46.528
AND, UH, GRANDMA'S
WATCHING PROJECT RUNWAY,

19:46.560 --> 19:47.834
SO CAN I JUST
WATCH THE GAME HERE?

19:47.870 --> 19:49.417
- ALL RIGHT, DREW,
COME ON IN.

19:49.460 --> 19:51.769
COME ON.
DREW, LISTEN TO ME.

19:51.810 --> 19:55.359
YOU ARE A BRAVERMAN, OKAY?

19:55.400 --> 19:56.355
IT'S GENETIC.

19:56.400 --> 19:57.844
YOU HAVE THE MOVES.

19:57.880 --> 19:59.495
YOU KNOW WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT?

19:59.540 --> 20:01.508
THEY'RE IN YOU.

20:01.540 --> 20:04.429
- YEAH, UM, THAT'S WHAT
I'M WORRIED ABOUT, ACTUALLY.

20:04.470 --> 20:05.471
- LISTEN,
JUST GO AND CHECK IT OUT.

20:05.510 --> 20:06.852
IF IT'S HELL ON EARTH,
WE'LL COME BACK HERE,

20:06.890 --> 20:08.505
WE'LL WATCH
THE REST OF THE GAME, OKAY?

20:08.550 --> 20:10.029
- I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S JUST...

20:10.070 --> 20:11.378
- I'M GONNA DRIVE YOU, OKAY?

20:11.410 --> 20:12.513
IT'S SETTLED.
ALL RIGHT, HEY, HADDIE.

20:12.550 --> 20:14.927
YOU ARE GONNA STAY HOME,
AND YOU ARE GONNA WATCH MAX.

20:14.970 --> 20:16.062
OKAY? 'CAUSE I'M GONNA
TAKE DREW TO THE DANCE.

20:16.110 --> 20:18.965
- I'D LIKE TO, BUT I ALREADY
CHECKED THIS WITH MOM,

20:19.010 --> 20:20.386
SO I'M GOING TO STEVE'S.

20:20.420 --> 20:21.796
DREW, HANG ON A SECOND.
HADDIE.

20:21.840 --> 20:23.387
HEY, LET ME TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND, OKAY?

20:23.420 --> 20:25.422
LOOK AT YOUR COUSIN, OKAY?
HE IS NEW AT THIS SCHOOL.

20:25.460 --> 20:28.384
HE'S OBVIOUSLY FEELING AWKWARD
ABOUT GOING TO THIS DANCE, OKAY?

20:28.430 --> 20:29.806
NOW, IF HE DOESN'T
PUT HIMSELF OUT THERE,

20:29.840 --> 20:31.489
HE COULD JUST BE
AN OUTCAST FOREVER.

20:31.540 --> 20:32.768
- FOR THE REST OF HIS LIFE?

20:32.810 --> 20:34.368
- FOR THE REST OF HIS LIFE.
FOREVER, OKAY?

20:34.400 --> 20:35.947
CAN YOU JUST
DO THIS FAVOR FOR HIM?

20:35.990 --> 20:38.458
WATCH YOUR BROTHER JUST FOR
ONE HOUR, ALL RIGHT? TOPS.

20:38.510 --> 20:40.478
- EXCUSE ME.
OKAY.

20:40.510 --> 20:41.431
- THANK YOU.
ALL RIGHT, DREW.

20:41.480 --> 20:42.617
COME ON, MAN.

20:42.650 --> 20:44.470
I'M GONNA SHOW YOU
HOW TO USE THE FISHERMAN

20:44.510 --> 20:45.477
TO REEL THAT GIRL IN.

20:45.520 --> 20:48.580
- EW.
- PLEASE DON'T.

20:48.620 --> 20:49.848
- HELLO.
- HEY.

20:49.900 --> 20:51.447
- HI, JABBAR.

20:51.490 --> 20:53.378
WE'RE SO EXCITED YOU'RE
SPENDING THE NIGHT WITH US.

20:53.420 --> 20:54.512
- YEAH.

20:54.560 --> 20:55.652
- SYDNEY, JABBAR'S HERE.
- OH, YAY!

20:55.700 --> 20:56.860
- HEY,
GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

20:56.910 --> 20:58.866
- I GOT A NEW
CALICO CRITTER PENGUIN.

20:58.910 --> 21:02.073
WANT TO SEE?
COME ON, LET'S GO.

21:02.120 --> 21:06.352
- WHAT, UH,
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

21:06.400 --> 21:08.015
- [clears throat]

21:08.050 --> 21:11.087
WELL, THAT'S THE VASE
SYDNEY WON'T ADMIT SHE BROKE.

21:11.130 --> 21:12.984
- SO YOU'RE JUST
LEAVING IT THERE?

21:13.030 --> 21:15.578
- FOR AS LONG AS IT TAKES.

21:15.610 --> 21:19.649
- YOU, UH, YOU REALIZE
THAT'S INSANE AND DANGEROUS?

21:19.690 --> 21:20.827
- WE'RE QUITE AWARE OF THAT.

21:20.860 --> 21:21.997
- THAT'S WHY
IT'S CORDONED OFF.

21:22.030 --> 21:22.997
FOR SAFETY.

21:23.040 --> 21:24.371
- OH.

21:24.420 --> 21:25.682
- YEAH.

21:25.730 --> 21:30.554
- OKAY. HA HA. OH, OKAY.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

21:30.590 --> 21:32.478
- JUST FEEL LIKE
THE BOOK WAS BETTER, YOU KNOW?

21:32.530 --> 21:35.977
ANYWAY, DID YOU SEE THE, UH,
EGGERS STORY IN MCSWEENEY'S?

21:36.010 --> 21:37.568
- I DON'T READ
MCSWEENEY'S ANYMORE.

21:37.600 --> 21:39.522
EVER SINCE THEY PASSED
ON MY LAST ESSAY.

21:39.570 --> 21:40.537
- MM.
KEEP UP THE GOOD WORK.

21:40.570 --> 21:41.559
- OH, THANKS.

21:41.610 --> 21:42.736
- I READ IT, ACTUALLY.

21:42.780 --> 21:43.747
I THOUGHT IT WAS BEAUTIFUL.

21:43.780 --> 21:45.748
SO FUNNY AND, YOU KNOW, SAD.

21:45.780 --> 21:46.883
- YOU READ MCSWEENEY'S?

21:46.920 --> 21:48.535
- THAT'S IMPRESSIVE.

21:48.580 --> 21:50.502
- OH, YEAH, WELL,

21:50.550 --> 21:52.097
I HAD SOMEBODY HELP ME
WITH THE BIG WORDS.

21:52.130 --> 21:53.097
THERE YOU GO.

21:53.130 --> 21:56.679
- THANKS.

21:56.720 --> 21:58.859
- YOU WANT ME TO GO TO SCHOOL
WITH THOSE DOUCHES?

21:58.900 --> 22:00.060
- WELL, NOT EVERYBODY'S
GONNA BE LIKE THAT,

22:00.110 --> 22:01.657
AND JUST, YOU KNOW,
THINK OF IT AS A WAY

22:01.690 --> 22:04.409
TO EXPAND YOUR REPERTOIRE
OF OBNOXIOUS BEHAVIOR.

22:04.460 --> 22:06.416
- SARAH?

22:06.460 --> 22:07.973
- JIM.

22:08.010 --> 22:09.489
- HEY. HOW YOU DOING?
- OH, MY GOODNESS.

22:09.530 --> 22:11.077
- I CAN'T BELIEï¬IE/IYOU'RE HERE.

22:11.120 --> 22:12.769
- THIS IS SUCH A--
THIS IS, LIKE, A SIGN.

22:12.810 --> 22:14.846
LIKE IN THE ALCHEMIST,
YOU KNOW?

22:14.880 --> 22:16.108
YOU READ THAT BOOK
THAT I GAVE YOU?

22:16.160 --> 22:18.628
- I HAVEN'T, BUT I
REALLY LOOK FORWARD TO IT.

22:18.680 --> 22:19.635
- OH.

22:19.680 --> 22:20.635
- UM...

22:20.680 --> 22:23.126
- THANK YOU FOR COMING.

22:23.160 --> 22:26.027
- UM, I HAD SUCH
A NICE TIME LAST TIME.

22:26.060 --> 22:28.403
- YEAH. IT WAS--IT'S BEEN
A WHILE SINCE LAST TIME.

22:28.450 --> 22:29.576
- THIS IS MY DAUGHTER,
AMBER.

22:29.620 --> 22:30.518
- OH, HEY, NICE TO MEET YOU.

22:30.550 --> 22:32.518
YOU KNOW,
I MET YOUR BROTHER, BRIEFLY.

22:32.550 --> 22:34.029
NO PUN INTENDED.
- WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

22:34.070 --> 22:36.550
- WELL--
[both stammering]

22:36.590 --> 22:38.137
- JIM AND I
WENT TO HIGH SCHOOL TOGETHER.

22:38.180 --> 22:39.624
- IT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

22:39.660 --> 22:40.934
- LONG TIME AGO.
YOU LOOK GREAT.

22:40.980 --> 22:42.936
- THANK YOU.
- SO, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

22:42.980 --> 22:44.527
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
WHAT AM I DOING HERE?

22:44.570 --> 22:45.525
YOU DON'T KNOW?

22:45.570 --> 22:46.946
- AND WITHOUT FURTHER ADO,

22:46.980 --> 22:48.527
OUR GUEST OF HONOR.

22:48.570 --> 22:51.801
[applause]

22:51.850 --> 22:53.431
- THANK YOU.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

22:53.470 --> 22:54.676
- THANKS, PROFESSOR.
THANK YOU.

22:54.710 --> 22:56.439
WELL, I HAVE A FEELING
THAT TONIGHT

22:56.990 --> 22:58.639
IS GONNA BE A VERY,

22:59.550 --> 23:02.121
VERY SPECIAL NIGHT.

23:02.170 --> 23:05.059
- OH, BOY.
- NIGHTMARE.

23:08.660 --> 23:10.651
- "THE GLOWING, RED EMBERS

23:10.690 --> 23:15.138
OF A FLAME
THAT NEVER BURNED."

23:15.180 --> 23:17.694
[applause]

23:17.740 --> 23:19.628
THANK YOU.

23:19.670 --> 23:20.762
SO, I HAVE A NEW ONE

23:20.810 --> 23:24.155
FROM, UH, ANOTHER COLLECTION
I'M PUTTING TOGETHER.

23:24.190 --> 23:25.771
UH, THE COLLECTION'S
GONNA BE CALLED

23:25.810 --> 23:29.462
THE ONE THAT GOT AWAY...
TWICE.

23:29.510 --> 23:30.738
ALTHOUGH, AFTER TONIGHT,

23:30.780 --> 23:34.056
I MIGHT RE-TITLE IT
THREE TIMES THE CHARM.

23:34.100 --> 23:37.501
THIS IS CALLED
ORCHID BLOOMING.

23:37.550 --> 23:39.996
"PARCHED GROUND

23:40.030 --> 23:42.828
"WELCOMES THE STORM.

23:42.860 --> 23:46.136
"MOIST, WET PETALS

23:46.180 --> 23:47.624
"SLOWLY OPEN,

23:47.660 --> 23:50.834
"BECKONING THE THUNDER,

23:50.870 --> 23:54.567
"YEARNING, SHUDDERING,

23:54.600 --> 23:59.253
"ELECT RIC, LIGHTNING.

23:59.290 --> 24:01.986
THE PINK ORCHID BLOOMS."

24:02.020 --> 24:03.464
- IT'S ABOUT FLOWERS, RIGHT?

24:03.510 --> 24:06.126
- I THINK IT MIGHT
BE ABOUT YOUR VAG.

24:06.160 --> 24:07.957
- "...IS READY
TO SPRAY ITS LOVE."

24:07.990 --> 24:12.131
- MM.
THAT IS DAMN GOOD BEER.

24:12.170 --> 24:14.582
- YEAH.
- SURE YOU DON'T WANT ONE?

24:14.620 --> 24:15.655
- WELL, UH,
ASSEMBLYMAN FORTUNATO...

24:15.690 --> 24:16.657
- PLEASE. MATT.

24:16.690 --> 24:18.578
- WELL,
YOU KNOW WHY WE'RE HERE.

24:18.620 --> 24:20.861
WE WANT YOU TO ENDORSE
ASSEMBLYWOMAN BOWSER.

24:20.900 --> 24:22.891
- SHE'S GOING UP AGAINST
SOME VERY POWERFUL PEOPLE.

24:22.940 --> 24:26.592
WITH LONG MEMORIES.

24:26.630 --> 24:27.938
- SO LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.

24:27.980 --> 24:30.039
WHY DID YOU RUN?
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

24:30.080 --> 24:31.809
- THE VERY FIRST TIME
THAT YOU RAN FOR OFFICE,

24:31.840 --> 24:33.603
WHY'D YOU DO IT?

24:33.640 --> 24:35.779
- WELL, I--I GUESS
I WANTED TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

24:35.810 --> 24:36.742
- MM-HMM.

24:36.780 --> 24:38.702
YOU RAN BECAUSE
THAT REFINERY IN RICHMOND

24:38.750 --> 24:41.981
WAS DUMPING HUNDREDS OF GALLONS
OF WASTE IN THE AQUIFER.

24:42.030 --> 24:45.887
REMEMBER?

24:45.930 --> 24:47.818
SEE, I WORKED FOR THE STATE
WATER BUREAU AT THE TIME,

24:47.860 --> 24:50.203
AND THIS MAN
GOT THAT PLANT SHUT DOWN ALONE.

24:50.240 --> 24:51.207
BY HIMSELF. COMPLETELY.

24:51.240 --> 24:52.753
- THAT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

24:52.800 --> 24:55.587
- DUDE, I KNOW.
IT WAS A WHILE AGO, DUDE.

24:55.630 --> 24:57.200
ANYWAY, HERE'S THE DEAL.

24:57.250 --> 24:59.662
ASSEMBLYWOMAN BOWSER, SHE WANTS
TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE TOO.

24:59.700 --> 25:01.691
YOU KNOW, HER OPPONENTS
MIGHT TWIT AND TALK ON--

25:01.740 --> 25:03.947
- TWEET.
- IT'S "TWEET."

25:03.980 --> 25:07.700
- T--WHATEVER,
THAT POLLUTION IS BAD,

25:07.740 --> 25:09.844
BUT, YOU KNOW, SHE ACTUALLY HAS
A PLAN TO DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT,

25:09.880 --> 25:13.156
A SOLID PLAN, STARTING WITH
BETTER REGULATION OF WATERWAYS.

25:13.200 --> 25:14.576
- YOU KNOW I LIKE HER, RIGHT?

25:14.610 --> 25:16.532
- I DO.
I KNOW THAT YOU LIKE HER.

25:16.580 --> 25:18.548
BUT...

25:18.580 --> 25:21.140
THE THING IS
IS SHE CAN'T DO IT ALONE.

25:21.170 --> 25:24.139
SEE, WE NEED YOUR HELP.

25:32.660 --> 25:34.662
- YOU KNOW, I'VE NEVER
REALLY GOTTEN THE HANG

25:34.700 --> 25:37.669
OF THIS WHOLE
FORK, SPOON TECHNIQUE.

25:37.700 --> 25:40.043
- HA. WELL,
THERE'S A TRICK THAT I LEARNED

25:40.090 --> 25:42.012
WHEN I WENT TO ITALY.

25:42.050 --> 25:44.678
AND THAT IS
ORDER THE RAVIOLI.

25:44.710 --> 25:46.052
- MM.
- MM?

25:46.090 --> 25:47.569
- YOU WENT TO ITALY?

25:47.610 --> 25:49.749
- MM-HMM.
JUST FOR A FEW WEEKS.

25:49.780 --> 25:51.987
JABBAR LOVED IT.

25:52.030 --> 25:54.169
YOU SHOULD HAVE HEARD HIM

25:54.200 --> 25:56.373
SING O SOLE MIO
WITH THE GONDOLIER.

25:56.410 --> 25:58.332
IT WAS REALLY CUTE.

25:58.380 --> 26:01.065
- MAN, I WISH I HAD.

26:06.040 --> 26:07.029
[cell phone rings]

26:07.080 --> 26:09.389
OOH.

26:09.420 --> 26:10.864
SORRY.
IT'S MY SISTER.

26:10.910 --> 26:12.047
HELLO.

26:12.080 --> 26:13.638
- HI. UM,
I'M SO SORRY TO BOTHER YOU,

26:13.670 --> 26:15.114
BUT IT'S JABBAR.
- I WANT TO GO HOME.

26:15.150 --> 26:16.185
- HE WANTS TO GO HOME.

26:16.220 --> 26:17.630
- OKAY.
HE'S OKAY, THOUGH, YEAH?

26:17.670 --> 26:18.944
- HE'S UPSET ABOUT SOMETHING.

26:18.990 --> 26:20.218
HE WON'T TELL ME
WHAT'S HAPPENING,

26:20.260 --> 26:22.012
BUT HE SAYS
IT'S AN EMERGENCY.

26:22.060 --> 26:23.368
- OKAY,
WE'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

26:23.400 --> 26:24.367
- OKAY, GREAT.
SEE YOU SOON.

26:24.410 --> 26:25.672
- ALL RIGHT.
- WHAT HAPPENED?

26:25.720 --> 26:27.676
- JABBAR WANTS TO GO HOME.

26:27.720 --> 26:30.188
I THINK HE'S SCARED.
- [laughs]

26:30.240 --> 26:31.207
- CHECK PLEASE.

26:31.240 --> 26:33.856
- [sighs]
ALL RIGHT.

26:33.900 --> 26:36.653
LET'S JUST DROWN OUR SORROWS
IN SOME JUNK FOOD AND BASEBALL.

26:36.690 --> 26:38.271
SHOULD BE ABLE
TO CATCH THOSE LATE INNINGS.

26:38.320 --> 26:39.389
- HEY, HOW'D IT GO?

26:39.420 --> 26:42.935
- WELL, I TOOK YOUR DAD'S
ADVICE ABOUT CONFIDENCE.

26:42.980 --> 26:45.665
I WENT UP,
I ASKED HER TO DANCE,

26:45.700 --> 26:46.667
AND SHE SHOT ME DOWN.

26:46.700 --> 26:47.564
SAID SHE DIDN'T WANT TO,

26:47.600 --> 26:49.283
LIKE, LEAVE HER FRIEND,
OR SOMETHING,

26:49.330 --> 26:50.354
WHEN I ASKED HER TO DANCE.

26:50.400 --> 26:52.948
- WELL, YOU KNOW, MAYBE, UM,

26:52.990 --> 26:54.389
HER FRIEND WAS JEALOUS,
OR SOMETHING.

26:54.440 --> 26:55.919
LIKE, MAYBE
HER FRIEND LIKED YOU.

26:55.950 --> 26:58.885
I DON'T KNOW.
SORRY. UM...

26:58.920 --> 27:02.686
OKAY, I'M GONNA GO.
- YOU CAN'T GO.

27:02.720 --> 27:05.336
- UM, MAX IS IN BED
AND YOU'RE HOME.

27:05.380 --> 27:06.586
- YEAH, WELL,
MAX COULD WAKE UP,

27:06.620 --> 27:09.748
AND I MIGHT HAVE TO LEAVE
ON AN EMERGENCY OR SOMETHING.

27:09.800 --> 27:11.415
YOU CAN'T GO.
YOU HAVE TO STAY HERE.

27:11.450 --> 27:12.724
- DAD?
- YEAH.

27:12.760 --> 27:14.000
- ARE YOU SERIOUSLY
GONNA KEEP ME HERE

27:14.040 --> 27:16.008
BECAUSE I'M WEARING
THIS STUPID BRA?

27:16.040 --> 27:18.349
- OF COURSE NOT.
IT'S A BRA, SO...

27:18.390 --> 27:20.358
YES, I AM.

27:20.390 --> 27:22.449
- OKAY.

27:22.500 --> 27:23.831
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT?

27:23.880 --> 27:25.700
IF YOU DON'T WANT ME
TO LEAVE THE HOUSE

27:25.740 --> 27:26.843
WHILE I'M WEARING THIS BRA...
- HADDIE.

27:26.880 --> 27:27.949
- THEN YOU DON'T
HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT IT.

27:27.990 --> 27:29.014
- HADDIE,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

27:29.060 --> 27:31.153
- I'M TRYING
TO MAKE YOU HAPPY, DAD.

27:31.200 --> 27:32.360
IF YOU DON'T WANT ME
TO LEAVE WEARING THIS,

27:32.400 --> 27:33.719
THEN I DON'T
HAVE TO WEAR IT.

27:33.750 --> 27:34.956
YOU CAN REST EASY,

27:34.990 --> 27:35.854
AND I'LL SEE YOU AT 11:30.

27:35.890 --> 27:38.472
- HADDIE, GET BACK
IN HERE RIGHT NOW.

27:38.510 --> 27:39.829
- WHAT?
WE MADE A DEAL.

27:39.860 --> 27:41.020
- HADDIE,
IF YOU LEAVE THIS HOU--

27:41.070 --> 27:43.277
[door slams]

27:43.310 --> 27:45.961
[sighs]

27:56.740 --> 27:58.833
WANT A SODA?

28:02.230 --> 28:03.367
[knock at door]

28:04.400 --> 28:06.265
- HI. SORRY
TO INTERRUPT YOUR DATE.

28:06.300 --> 28:07.744
I--I DON'T--
- WHERE IS HE?

28:07.780 --> 28:09.099
- MOMMY, CROSBY.

28:09.130 --> 28:10.472
- HEY.

28:10.510 --> 28:12.717
WHAT HAPPENED, BUDDY?

28:12.760 --> 28:14.307
- CAN WE GO HOME NOW?

28:14.340 --> 28:17.229
- WHAT HAPPENED?

28:17.280 --> 28:19.680
- NOTHING.

28:23.040 --> 28:23.859
- WHAT'S THE MATTER?

28:23.900 --> 28:26.767
- I JUST REALLY
NEED TO GO HOME NOW.

28:26.800 --> 28:30.008
- OKAY, UM, IS IT SOMETHING
YOU NEED TO DO AT HOME?

28:30.050 --> 28:31.005
- YEAH.

28:31.050 --> 28:31.835
- YEAH?

28:31.880 --> 28:36.533
- I NEED TO GO POOP
AT HOME BAD.

28:36.570 --> 28:41.360
- OKAY.
IT'S--HE'S--OKAY.

28:41.400 --> 28:42.401
- YEAH.

28:44.440 --> 28:46.123
- HEY, MAX,
STAY IN THE BACK.

28:46.170 --> 28:47.751
- NOPE! TOO LATE.

28:47.790 --> 28:49.337
- DREW, CAN YOU ASK HIM
TO GET IN THE BACK?

28:49.380 --> 28:53.100
LISTEN TO DREW.
- JUST--COME ON.

28:53.140 --> 28:54.994
- HEY.
- OH, HI, ADAM.

28:55.040 --> 28:57.349
- HEY, IS, UH, IS HADDIE HERE,
BY ANY CHANCE?

28:57.390 --> 28:58.834
- YEAH, SHE'S UPSTAIRS
WITH STEVE.

28:58.870 --> 29:00.417
- OH.
- YEAH, IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

29:00.460 --> 29:01.381
- YEAH, YEAH.

29:01.420 --> 29:03.763
UH, WE JUST HAD
A SMALL EMERGENCY AT HOME,

29:03.810 --> 29:05.038
AND SHE HAS TO--YEAH.

29:05.080 --> 29:06.456
- OH, ANYTHING WE CAN DO?
- NO, NO, THANKS.

29:06.500 --> 29:08.468
YOU MIND IF I JUST,
UH, JUST GO GET HER?

29:08.500 --> 29:09.467
- SURE.
- WHERE IS SHE?

29:09.500 --> 29:10.876
- OKAY. JUST UPSTAIRS.

29:10.920 --> 29:12.535
- UPSTAIRS?
IS THAT WHERE STEVE'S ROOM IS?

29:12.570 --> 29:14.879
- YEAH.

29:15.890 --> 29:18.506
[distant rock music playing]

29:19.930 --> 29:21.500
- HELLO?

29:21.550 --> 29:23.541
[knocking on door]

29:25.590 --> 29:26.921
- HEY, ADAM, WHAT'S UP?

29:26.970 --> 29:28.483
- MR. BRAVERMAN.

29:28.520 --> 29:29.589
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

29:29.620 --> 29:32.589
- YOU ARE COMING WITH ME
RIGHT NOW.

29:32.630 --> 29:35.861
- NO, I'M NOT.

29:35.910 --> 29:38.071
- YES, YOU ARE.

29:38.120 --> 29:39.075
HADDIE.

29:39.120 --> 29:40.428
- HMM?

29:40.460 --> 29:42.940
- OKAY--I'M SORRY.

29:42.980 --> 29:44.083
- RIGHT NOW. COME ON.

29:44.120 --> 29:45.530
- IT'S ALL GOOD.
- YOU HAVE EVERYTHING?

29:45.570 --> 29:46.491
- I'LL SEE YOU LATER, ADAM.

29:46.540 --> 29:48.258
- MR. BRAVERMAN.

29:48.300 --> 29:51.884
- RIDICULOUS.
- GET DOWNSTAIRS.

29:51.920 --> 29:53.547
THANK YOU.
- THANKS FOR COMING OVER.

29:53.580 --> 29:54.808
- OKAY. THANKS.
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

29:54.860 --> 29:55.815
- BYE.

29:55.860 --> 29:56.815
- HEY.
- WHAT?

29:56.860 --> 29:57.929
- HEY.
- WHAT?

29:57.960 --> 30:00.201
DON'T TOUCH ME.
DON'T TALK TO ME.

30:00.240 --> 30:01.446
- OKAY, GO.
GET IN THE BACK SEAT.

30:01.480 --> 30:02.924
GET IN THE BACK SEAT.
- DON'T TALK TO ME.

30:02.970 --> 30:05.245
- I DON'T THINK
I CAN DO THIS.

30:05.280 --> 30:06.963
- YOU CAN DO IT, HONEY.

30:07.010 --> 30:08.864
- YEAH, AUNT JULIA'S
IS A GREAT PLACE TO GO.

30:08.910 --> 30:11.049
YOU JUST DON'T
FOCUS SO MUCH ON THE GOING.

30:11.080 --> 30:13.287
MAYBE, UM--OOH,
LET'S SING A SONG.

30:13.320 --> 30:14.969
JASMINE,
DO YOU KNOW A SONG?

30:15.020 --> 30:17.113
- I KNOW A SONG.

30:17.160 --> 30:21.369
- THE WHEELS ON THE BUS
GO ROUND AND ROUND

30:21.400 --> 30:23.254
all: ROUND AND ROUND

30:23.300 --> 30:24.608
ROUND AND ROUND

30:24.650 --> 30:27.915
THE WHEELS ON THE BUS
GO ROUND AND ROUND

30:27.960 --> 30:30.576
ALL THROUGH THE TOWN

30:30.620 --> 30:34.920
AND THE DOORS ON THE BUS
GO OPEN AND SHUT

30:34.970 --> 30:36.278
- AND THE PEOPLE BUST OUT

30:36.310 --> 30:38.346
LIKE CRAZY ENGLISH
SOCCER FANS

30:38.380 --> 30:39.586
SOCCER FANS

30:39.630 --> 30:42.269
- [laughs]
THAT'S NOT HOW THE SONG GOES.

30:44.670 --> 30:46.558
I DID IT.

30:46.600 --> 30:48.283
- YEAH, YOU DID IT.

30:48.320 --> 30:49.287
ALL RIGHT!

30:49.330 --> 30:50.558
- YOU DID. YEAH.

30:50.600 --> 30:52.397
- GOOD WORK.
- THERE YOU GO. NICE JOB.

30:52.430 --> 30:54.227
- "ENGLISH SOCCER FANS"
ALWAYS WORKS.

31:00.410 --> 31:02.958
- [sighs]

31:02.990 --> 31:06.266
- I CAN'T GET OVER IT.

31:06.310 --> 31:08.096
JIM KAZINSKY.

31:08.140 --> 31:10.449
HE'S A PUBLISHED AUTHOR.

31:10.480 --> 31:16.453
HE USED TO COPY OFF ME
IN 10TH GRADE.

31:16.490 --> 31:18.526
- THAT'S COOL.

31:18.560 --> 31:21.620
WRITING A BUNCH OF POEMS

31:21.670 --> 31:26.039
ABOUT A BIG LOSER
GETTING LAID BY A HOT LADY.

31:26.090 --> 31:27.159
- YOU KNOW WHAT?
THAT'S NOT NICE.

31:27.190 --> 31:30.978
HE'S NOT A LOSER.
HE'S--HE'S SUCH A SPECIAL GUY.

31:31.020 --> 31:34.126
HE MIGHT NOT BE,
YOU KNOW, MY SOUL MATE,

31:34.160 --> 31:36.606
BUT HE'S...
HE'S TALENTED.

31:36.650 --> 31:39.369
- I GUESS I WAS PROBABLY
JUST GROSSED OUT

31:39.410 --> 31:40.638
THAT I HAD TO HEAR, LIKE,

31:40.690 --> 31:43.511
15 BILLION POEMS
ABOUT MY MOTHER'S VAGOOZLE.

31:43.550 --> 31:44.653
- YOU KNOW,
IT'S NOT THE POINT.

31:44.690 --> 31:47.306
THE POINT IS, THIS IS A GUY
WHO READ DYLAN THOMAS

31:47.350 --> 31:49.102
IN HIGH SCHOOL
AND WAS INSPIRED,

31:49.140 --> 31:50.698
AND THEN FOLLOWED HIS DREAM.

31:50.730 --> 31:53.415
AND LOOK AT WHAT HE'S ACHIEVED,
YOU KNOW?

31:53.460 --> 31:57.146
I MEAN, THAT'S WHAT
I WANT FOR YOU, YOU KNOW?

31:57.190 --> 31:58.669
THAT'S WHY I BROUGHT YOU
TO THIS SCHOOL.

31:58.700 --> 32:01.282
YOU--YOU JUST CAN'T
GIVE UP ON YOURSELF.

32:01.330 --> 32:03.639
I MEAN,
THAT'S LIVING PROOF.

32:03.680 --> 32:05.489
YOU JUST CAN'T--
YOU CAN'T GIVE UP ON YOURSELF.

32:16.580 --> 32:17.854
- ARE YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO STAY?

32:17.900 --> 32:20.687
- YEAH, WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE OF
CHUTES AND LADDERS TOURNAMENT.

32:20.730 --> 32:22.482
- OKAY.
GIVE ME A HUG.

32:22.520 --> 32:24.488
- TAKE NO PRISONERS.

32:24.520 --> 32:26.317
- 'KAY.

32:26.350 --> 32:27.419
COME ON.

32:27.460 --> 32:30.213
- OKAY. YOU WILL NOT
HEAR FROM ME AGAIN TONIGHT.

32:30.250 --> 32:31.387
- LET'S GO!
- THANKS.

32:31.430 --> 32:33.148
- COME ON, JULIA!
- OKAY. OKAY!

32:33.190 --> 32:35.112
- ENGLISH SOCCER FANS?

32:35.160 --> 32:36.115
- YEAH, WELL,
YOU STARTED IT

32:36.160 --> 32:38.537
WITH THE WHOLE DOORS
OPENING AND SHUTTING.

32:38.570 --> 32:40.219
- THAT'S HOW THE SONG GOES.

32:40.260 --> 32:41.704
- THAT'S NOT
HOW THE SONG GOES.

32:41.750 --> 32:43.331
- YES, IT IS.
- FOR REAL?

32:43.370 --> 32:45.122
- FOR REAL.
- OKAY.

32:45.170 --> 32:47.126
WELL, IT INSPIRED ME.

32:47.170 --> 32:50.446
- GOOD.

32:50.480 --> 32:53.062
IT INSPIRED YOU.

32:53.100 --> 32:56.342
- YOU INSPIRED ME.

32:56.380 --> 32:57.586
- I INSPIRED YOU?

32:57.630 --> 32:59.313
- YEAH.

32:59.350 --> 33:00.692
- REALLY?

33:00.730 --> 33:04.598
- BIG TIME.

33:04.630 --> 33:06.621
- ARE YOU TRYING
TO USE MY POO SONG

33:06.670 --> 33:10.538
AS A WAY TO MAKE YOUR MOVE?

33:10.570 --> 33:12.083
- YEAH.

33:12.120 --> 33:13.496
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

33:13.540 --> 33:15.701
- UM, I DON'T KNOW.

33:15.750 --> 33:18.674
WELL, YOU HAVEN'T
REALLY MADE A MOVE YET.

33:18.720 --> 33:21.359
CAN'T TELL YOU.

34:00.620 --> 34:04.169
- WHAT THE HELL
WERE YOU THINKING?

34:04.210 --> 34:05.723
- DAD, WHAT WAS I THINKING?

34:05.760 --> 34:07.728
I MEAN, WHAT--
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

34:07.760 --> 34:09.762
- I TOLD YOU TO STAY AT HOME,
AND YOU JUST TOOK OFF.

34:09.800 --> 34:11.722
- YEAH, WELL, YOU WERE
BEING TOTALLY UNREASONABLE.

34:11.770 --> 34:13.806
- WELL, I DON'T CARE IF
I'M BEING UNREASONABLE, HADDIE.

34:13.840 --> 34:15.569
YOU'RE 15 YEARS OLD

34:15.600 --> 34:16.874
AND YOU LIVE IN MY HOUSE,

34:16.910 --> 34:18.423
SO YOU DO WHAT I SAY
WHEN I SAY IT.

34:18.470 --> 34:20.700
- REALLY? I DO WHATEVER YOU SAY
NO MATTER WHAT?

34:20.740 --> 34:21.729
- YES. NO MATTER WHAT.

34:21.780 --> 34:23.463
- OKAY, SO IF YOU TELL ME
TO SHAVE MY HEAD,

34:23.500 --> 34:24.706
I HAVE TO DO IT?
- YES.

34:24.750 --> 34:26.502
- IF YOU TELL ME TO MURDER
SOMEBODY, THEN I HAVE TO DO IT?

34:26.540 --> 34:28.121
- YES.
KEEP IT COMING. COME ON.

34:28.160 --> 34:29.787
- DAD, IF YOU TELL ME
TO BURN THIS HOUSE DOWN,

34:29.820 --> 34:30.809
THEN I HAVE TO DO THAT?

34:30.860 --> 34:31.645
- YEAH, IF I TELL YOU
TO BURN DOWN THE HOUSE,

34:31.690 --> 34:32.884
YOU HAVE TO
BURN DOWN THE HOUSE.

34:32.930 --> 34:33.783
- DAD!

34:35.410 --> 34:36.786
OKAY.

34:39.660 --> 34:43.892
DAD, MOM TOLD ME THAT I
COULD GO TO STEVE'S HOUSE.

34:43.940 --> 34:46.386
THEN YOU TOLD ME
THAT I HAD TO STAY HOME

34:46.420 --> 34:47.762
AND WATCH MAX
FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

34:47.800 --> 34:49.768
AND I DID.
- RIGHT.

34:49.810 --> 34:51.664
- BUT THEN YOU CAME HOME
AND TOLD ME

34:51.710 --> 34:52.836
THAT I COULDN'T
GO TO STEVE'S HOUSE

34:52.880 --> 34:56.668
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T LIKE
THE KIND OF BRA I WAS WEARING.

35:00.200 --> 35:03.818
- I ADMIT THAT
THAT WAS, UH...

35:03.860 --> 35:06.818
INCONSISTENT.

35:06.860 --> 35:08.441
- INCONSISTENT?

35:08.480 --> 35:09.583
- I'M CONCERNED
ABOUT YOU, HADDIE.

35:09.620 --> 35:10.826
- YOU ARE A HYPOCRITE.

35:10.860 --> 35:14.444
YOU WOULD TOTALLY LET DREW
HANG OUT WITH HIS GIRLFRIEND.

35:14.490 --> 35:17.277
YOU WOULD DRIVE HIM TO HANG OUT
WITH HIS GIRLFRIEND.

35:17.320 --> 35:18.582
BUT BECAUSE I'M A GIRL,

35:18.630 --> 35:24.421
YOU TREAT ME
LIKE I'M 12 YEARS OLD.

35:24.460 --> 35:26.451
- IT'S BECAUSE
YOU'RE MY DAUGHTER.

35:29.470 --> 35:30.539
OKAY?
AND YOU'RE NOT WRONG.

35:30.570 --> 35:33.505
THERE IS A DOUBLE STANDARD.

35:33.540 --> 35:34.507
- YEAH.

35:34.540 --> 35:36.599
- AND IT'S NOT FAIR.

35:36.650 --> 35:37.878
- THANKS.

35:37.920 --> 35:42.755
- BUT THEN AGAIN,
NEITHER IS THE WORLD.

35:42.790 --> 35:44.519
- OKAY, WELL,
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

35:44.550 --> 35:46.654
- THAT'S THE WAY IT IS.

36:04.640 --> 36:08.508
- HELLO LAZY MORNING

36:12.540 --> 36:13.814
- MM.

36:13.860 --> 36:16.499
-OH

36:16.550 --> 36:19.587
WHERE COULD THE SUN BE
THIS AFTERNOON

36:19.620 --> 36:21.793
- HEY.

36:21.830 --> 36:23.411
- HEY.

36:23.450 --> 36:28.592
- OH LOOK
WHAT THE SUN DID

36:28.630 --> 36:33.283
IT TURNED A GRAY TO BLUE

36:33.320 --> 36:34.696
- OH, MAN.
IT'S 10:16.

36:34.740 --> 36:35.946
- OH, SO WHAT?

36:35.980 --> 36:37.595
- WELL, I TOLD JULIA

36:37.640 --> 36:40.256
THAT I'D PICK JABBAR UP
AT 10:30.

36:40.300 --> 36:41.631
- WELL, JUST BE
A FEW MINUTES LATE.

36:41.680 --> 36:43.568
- WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
JULIA HERE.

36:43.610 --> 36:45.817
YOU KNOW, MY CRAZY SISTER.

36:45.850 --> 36:49.741
SHE'LL USE THIS
AS A TEACHABLE MOMENT.

36:49.790 --> 36:51.473
PROBABLY HOLD JABBAR HOSTAGE

36:51.510 --> 36:53.683
UNTIL I LEARN TO BE PUNCTUAL.

36:53.720 --> 36:55.278
- I PROBABLY SHOULDN'T
GO WITH YOU, THEN,

36:55.310 --> 36:58.620
BECAUSE JABBAR WILL WONDER
WHY WE'RE STILL TOGETHER.

36:58.660 --> 36:59.627
- RIGHT.
- YEAH.

36:59.660 --> 37:01.582
- RIGHT. OKAY.

37:01.630 --> 37:03.279
UM, GOOD PLAN.

37:03.320 --> 37:05.288
I WILL GO SUPER FAST,

37:05.320 --> 37:07.697
AND THEN I WILL SEE YOU
IN A FEW MINUTES.

37:07.740 --> 37:09.492
- OKAY.

37:09.530 --> 37:13.773
- THAT WAS, UM,
REALLY FUN LAST NIGHT.

37:13.810 --> 37:16.256
I'LL BE BACK.

37:19.750 --> 37:22.605
- [groans]

37:22.650 --> 37:24.686
- [sighs]

37:24.720 --> 37:26.756
FINE. I DID IT.

37:26.790 --> 37:27.825
I BROKE THE VASE.

37:27.860 --> 37:29.339
ARE YOU HAPPY NOW?

37:29.380 --> 37:30.756
- NO, I'M NOT HAPPY.

37:30.800 --> 37:32.062
- YOU WON, OKAY?
YOU WON.

37:32.110 --> 37:34.340
- SWEETIE, IT'S NOT
ABOUT WINNING AND LOSING.

37:34.390 --> 37:35.345
IT'S ABOUT BEING HONEST.

37:35.390 --> 37:37.529
- YOU WIN. I LOSE.

37:37.560 --> 37:39.243
I'LL GO PICK IT UP.

37:41.120 --> 37:42.838
- OKAY.
- DAD, WHERE'S THE BROOM?

37:42.880 --> 37:45.428
- PANTRY.

37:46.740 --> 37:47.775
- ALL RIGHTY.

37:47.810 --> 37:49.801
- WHO WAS THAT PERSON?

37:49.850 --> 37:52.466
- I DIDN'T RECOGNIZE HER
AT ALL.

37:52.510 --> 37:53.295
IT'S FUNNY.

37:53.340 --> 37:54.534
- WHAT IS THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

37:54.580 --> 37:55.535
- [sighs]

37:55.580 --> 37:58.026
- YEAH.

37:58.060 --> 38:00.995
- JOEL.

38:01.030 --> 38:03.749
WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

38:13.840 --> 38:16.456
- NO, NO,
I'M NOT FALLING FOR THIS.

38:16.500 --> 38:18.946
YOU DROP THE BERKELEY COLLEGE
CATALOGUE IN FRONT OF ME

38:18.980 --> 38:20.629
AND YOU THINK I'M GONNA
GET ALL EXCITED,

38:20.670 --> 38:22.080
BUT THEN YOU'RE GONNA
BREAK MY HEART

38:22.120 --> 38:23.678
WHEN YOU TELL ME
YOU DECIDED NOT TO APPLY,

38:23.710 --> 38:26.508
SO I SAY...

38:26.540 --> 38:27.700
WHATEVER.

38:27.750 --> 38:28.717
- HUH.

38:28.750 --> 38:30.502
SO FIRST OF ALL,

38:30.540 --> 38:31.984
IT'S NOT REALLY
REVERSE PSYCHOLOGY

38:32.030 --> 38:33.782
IF YOU TELL ME
WHAT YOU'RE DOING,

38:33.820 --> 38:34.957
AND, SECOND OF ALL,

38:35.000 --> 38:37.719
IT'S NOT FOR ME.
IT'S FOR YOU.

38:37.760 --> 38:40.729
- WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

38:40.760 --> 38:44.764
- I THINK YOU
SHOULD APPLY TO BERKELEY.

38:44.800 --> 38:47.689
- WHAT?

38:47.730 --> 38:49.357
- WELL, WHY NOT?

38:49.390 --> 38:50.527
I MEAN, IF JIM KAZINSKY

38:50.560 --> 38:53.120
CAN GET PEOPLE ALL HOT
AND BOTHERED ABOUT HIS POETRY,

38:53.150 --> 38:56.529
THEN ANYTHING IS POSSIBLE,
RIGHT?

38:56.570 --> 38:59.539
JUST DON'T GIVE UP
ON YOURSELF EITHER, OKAY?

38:59.570 --> 39:03.916
- IT TOOK TOO LONG
TO SEE

39:03.960 --> 39:07.054
I WAS WRONG TO BELIEVE

39:07.100 --> 39:09.682
IN ME ONLY

39:13.900 --> 39:15.037
- HI THERE.

39:15.070 --> 39:16.037
- HEY.

39:16.070 --> 39:18.004
- HEY.
WHAT YA READING?

39:18.040 --> 39:20.793
I READ THAT ONE.

39:20.840 --> 39:24.697
- HOW'S THE, UH, ADJUSTMENT BACK
INTO FAMILY LIFE TREATING YOU?

39:24.740 --> 39:25.968
- IT'S GOOD.
- YEAH?

39:26.010 --> 39:27.591
- YUP.
I MISSED YOU.

39:27.640 --> 39:28.595
- I MISSED YOU TOO.

39:28.640 --> 39:29.777
- A LOT.

39:29.810 --> 39:31.732
- MM.

39:31.780 --> 39:34.601
- SO, UM...
- YEAH?

39:34.640 --> 39:37.712
- DENISE WANTS ME TO COME
WITH HER TO L.A. NEXT WEEK

39:37.750 --> 39:38.819
FOR A COUPLE OF FUNDRAISERS.

39:38.850 --> 39:40.408
- OH. OKAY.

39:40.440 --> 39:41.919
- YEAH.
- THAT'S COOL.

39:41.960 --> 39:43.689
- SHE ALSO OFFERED ME
A FULL-TIME JOB

39:43.720 --> 39:47.781
AS HER
COMMUNICATIONS DIRECTOR.

39:47.830 --> 39:49.752
- UH, CONGRATULATIONS.
THAT'S GREAT.

39:49.800 --> 39:52.485
UM, WHAT'D YOU SAY?

39:52.520 --> 39:54.078
- WELL, I TOLD HER
THAT I WOULD THINK ABOUT IT,

39:54.110 --> 39:55.793
AND I WOULD TALK TO YOU.

39:55.840 --> 39:59.139
- SO YOU WANT TO DO IT?

39:59.180 --> 40:02.525
- KIND OF.
I JUST--I DON'T KNOW.

40:02.570 --> 40:04.219
I MEAN, HONEY,
I--I LOVE OUR KIDS,

40:04.260 --> 40:06.569
AND I LOVE YOU
AND I LOVE BEING A MOM.

40:06.610 --> 40:07.918
I LOVE ALL OF THAT.

40:07.950 --> 40:09.770
BUT, HONESTLY,
WHEN I WAS THERE,

40:09.820 --> 40:12.914
I FELT SO--
I FELT SO ALIVE,

40:12.960 --> 40:15.053
AND--AND IT WAS
JUST AMAZING.

40:15.100 --> 40:16.681
IT WAS LIKE
I WAS BEING SEEN

40:16.720 --> 40:18.028
FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN SO LONG, YOU KNOW?

40:18.070 --> 40:21.471
- I GET IT.
I GET IT.

40:21.520 --> 40:22.305
OKAY?

40:22.350 --> 40:23.851
BUT I WANT YOU TO KNOW
I SEE YOU.

40:23.900 --> 40:24.867
- I KNOW.

40:24.900 --> 40:25.821
I KNOW YOU DO.

40:25.870 --> 40:28.589
BUT YOU--YOU SEE ME
IN A DIFFERENT WAY.

40:28.630 --> 40:31.724
- I KNOW.

40:31.770 --> 40:32.737
- ALL RIGHT.
- WHAT?

40:32.770 --> 40:33.976
- SO WE'LL FIGURE THIS OUT.

40:34.010 --> 40:35.216
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

40:35.260 --> 40:37.774
UM, YOU KNOW,

40:37.810 --> 40:39.084
I'LL NEED SOME HELP HERE
AT THE HOUSE,

40:39.120 --> 40:41.634
AND I'LL, UH--
I'LL CALL MY MOM.

40:41.680 --> 40:42.749
YOU KNOW,
I THINK THAT SHE'LL BE UP

40:42.780 --> 40:44.259
FOR STAYING HERE
A COUPLE NIGHTS A WEEK.

40:44.300 --> 40:46.643
AND YOU KNOW, I NEED TO GET
SOMEBODY ON THE HOOK

40:46.680 --> 40:49.478
TO MAKE SURE MAX
MAKES IT TO ALL HIS THERAPIES

40:49.510 --> 40:51.478
AND HADDIE GETS TO ALL
HER SPORTING EVENTS, BUT,

40:51.510 --> 40:53.751
UM, YOU KNOW, AND I CAN ALSO
COME HOME FROM WORK EARLY

40:53.790 --> 40:54.757
ONCE OR TWICE A WEEK,

40:54.790 --> 40:56.269
AND I CAN START TO,
YOU KNOW,

40:56.310 --> 40:57.857
WORK MORE FROM HOME
IN THE MORNING.

40:57.900 --> 40:58.889
WE'LL WORK IT OUT.

40:58.930 --> 41:01.000
GET SOME GROCERIES DELIVERED.
FIGURE IT OUT.

41:01.040 --> 41:03.725
- YEAH.
NO, YOU KNOW--

41:03.770 --> 41:04.998
- WHAT?

41:05.040 --> 41:08.999
- HONEY, UM,
THIS ISN'T THE RIGHT TIME.

41:09.050 --> 41:11.189
I--I'M NOT GONNA DO IT.
- KRISTINA.

41:11.220 --> 41:13.529
- THIS ISN'T THE RIGHT TIME.
MAX AND HADDIE NEED ME HERE.

41:13.570 --> 41:14.844
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I WAS THINKING.

41:14.880 --> 41:16.632
- KRISTINA...
- NO, NO.

41:16.680 --> 41:17.601
- I DON'T WANT YOU
TO LOOK BACK ON THIS

41:17.640 --> 41:18.914
AND FEEL LIKE YOU
MISSED OUT ON SOMETHING.

41:18.950 --> 41:20.815
- I WON'T, I WON'T.

41:20.850 --> 41:22.784
UH, THIS IS A NO-BRAINER,
YOU KNOW?

41:22.820 --> 41:24.788
I MEAN,
THERE'LL BE OTHER CAMPAIGNS,

41:24.820 --> 41:30.611
AND OUR KIDS ARE ONLY
GONNA BE KIDS FOR SO LONG.

41:30.660 --> 41:31.649
AND I CAN DO IT LATER.

41:31.690 --> 41:35.205
- AND IT AIN'T ABOUT
LOSING YOUR MIND

41:35.250 --> 41:37.002
- ARE YOU SURE?

41:37.040 --> 41:39.008
- YES, I'M SURE.

41:39.040 --> 41:41.736
- BUT IF YOU HAPPEN TO
THAT'S FINE

41:41.770 --> 41:44.876
- ALL RIGHT. WHY DON'T YOU
TELL ME ABOUT THIS MEETING?

41:44.910 --> 41:46.969
- UM, IT WAS AWESOME.

41:47.020 --> 41:47.975
IT WAS SO COOL.

41:48.020 --> 41:49.738
I MEAN, YOU WOULD HAVE BEEN
SO PROUD OF ME.

41:49.780 --> 41:51.839
I, UM...

41:51.880 --> 41:53.814
I WAS AWESOME.

41:53.850 --> 41:55.078
